1
00:00:00,790 --> 00:00:09,200
<b>Hotel Del Luna Blu-ray Disc 5</b>
Subtitle re-timing by Jharel

2
00:00:55,514 --> 00:00:59,394
It's not that wonderful
to be in hell together.

3
00:01:02,813 --> 00:01:04,523
<i>What I have is hell.</i>

4
00:01:07,526 --> 00:01:08,606
Goodbye.

5
00:01:09,528 --> 00:01:10,778
Chan-sung.

6
00:01:15,743 --> 00:01:17,043
She's gone.

7
00:01:50,903 --> 00:01:51,903
Hey.

8
00:01:53,280 --> 00:01:54,490
Can you see that?

9
00:01:57,284 --> 00:01:58,334
-I'm sorry.
-I'm sorry.

10
00:01:58,661 --> 00:02:00,081
Let's go.

11
00:02:01,914 --> 00:02:03,964
I didn't know a place like this
existed in Myeong-dong.

12
00:02:04,041 --> 00:02:06,001
-Me neither.
-Let's go.

13
00:02:35,823 --> 00:02:38,283
Mr. Koo must feel very flustered.

14
00:02:38,576 --> 00:02:40,366
He worked with us for quite some time.

15
00:02:40,452 --> 00:02:42,912
Shouldn't you at least leave him a text?

16
00:02:42,997 --> 00:02:45,167
I gave him something else instead.

17
00:02:45,332 --> 00:02:48,712
I gave him a severance pay
and a dismissal notice.

18
00:02:53,591 --> 00:02:55,261
<i>I guess you just think of him</i>

19
00:02:55,759 --> 00:02:59,559
<i>as the 99th human who worked for you.</i>

20
00:03:00,556 --> 00:03:03,766
<i>No, Chan-sung is special.</i>

21
00:03:04,894 --> 00:03:06,944
I don't want to become weak-hearted.

22
00:03:08,647 --> 00:03:11,067
I'm trying to be stronger.

23
00:03:11,984 --> 00:03:14,904
I haven't heard
such sentimental words from you in...

24
00:03:15,404 --> 00:03:19,534
No, this is the first time in 500 years.

25
00:03:20,367 --> 00:03:21,407
Five hundred years?

26
00:03:22,661 --> 00:03:25,081
Has it been that long since you died?

27
00:03:25,164 --> 00:03:27,084
What are you still doing here
for 500 years?

28
00:03:27,166 --> 00:03:31,166
I shouldn't be hearing that from a ghost
who's been here twice as long.

29
00:03:31,253 --> 00:03:34,173
I can't leave
because I'm tied to the Moon Tree.

30
00:03:34,256 --> 00:03:38,296
I can't leave because I still have
shame to clear up in this world.

31
00:03:38,594 --> 00:03:41,854
I can't face my ancestors
in the afterlife like this.

32
00:03:42,473 --> 00:03:45,313
Even if you go to the afterlife,
you won't meet your ancestors.

33
00:03:45,392 --> 00:03:47,772
They must have reincarnated
several times already.

34
00:03:48,354 --> 00:03:49,774
You're worrying for nothing.

35
00:03:49,855 --> 00:03:53,975
I can just remain at the hotel
and continue to worry for nothing.

36
00:03:54,068 --> 00:03:55,858
But will you be all right like this?

37
00:03:56,904 --> 00:03:58,994
Will you be all right
giving up your chance

38
00:03:59,073 --> 00:04:01,493
to go to the afterlife peacefully
through Mr. Koo?

39
00:04:04,745 --> 00:04:06,405
They won't let me go peacefully.

40
00:04:08,374 --> 00:04:10,834
In the future, try to speed up

41
00:04:10,918 --> 00:04:13,048
and take care of your shame
left in this life.

42
00:04:13,128 --> 00:04:14,798
There won't be much time.

43
00:04:15,464 --> 00:04:19,014
If you can't solve it, take the bus
to the afterlife without regrets.

44
00:04:20,219 --> 00:04:22,599
What about the guests?
Did you send them off properly?

45
00:04:22,680 --> 00:04:24,850
We moved them with the help
of the Grim Reapers.

46
00:04:24,932 --> 00:04:27,692
Although there was some confusion
due to the sudden move.

47
00:04:29,561 --> 00:04:33,571
Those of you who have no regrets
and can leave right now.

48
00:04:33,857 --> 00:04:35,477
Please take this bus.

49
00:04:35,567 --> 00:04:38,147
Those of you who can't leave
because of your resentments.

50
00:04:38,237 --> 00:04:39,947
Please standby here.

51
00:04:40,030 --> 00:04:41,120
TO THIS LIFE, TO THE AFTERLIFE

52
00:04:41,198 --> 00:04:42,698
You must not get confused.

53
00:04:42,783 --> 00:04:45,743
Once you get on the bus,
you can't turn back.

54
00:04:46,078 --> 00:04:48,158
Are you going to the afterlife?

55
00:04:48,247 --> 00:04:50,787
My older child went to college
and is doing well now.

56
00:04:51,041 --> 00:04:52,381
It's time to leave.

57
00:04:55,045 --> 00:04:58,415
You went to wake up your son
in his dreams every morning.

58
00:04:58,507 --> 00:04:59,927
I'm glad he finally went to college.

59
00:05:00,009 --> 00:05:01,219
Have a good trip.

60
00:05:06,557 --> 00:05:08,927
TO THIS LIFE, TO THE AFTERLIFE

61
00:05:11,645 --> 00:05:14,185
You must choose a line.

62
00:05:14,273 --> 00:05:18,153
I can't decide whether to go
to the afterlife or stay here.

63
00:05:18,235 --> 00:05:20,695
Did you finish the novel
you were working on?

64
00:05:21,405 --> 00:05:26,405
No. I couldn't finish it when I was alive.
I guess I can't finish it when I'm dead.

65
00:05:27,119 --> 00:05:28,329
I had better go.

66
00:05:34,501 --> 00:05:35,921
Should I stay and write it?

67
00:05:40,841 --> 00:05:42,971
This guest can't make up his mind.

68
00:05:43,302 --> 00:05:44,602
He won't be able to leave.

69
00:05:45,596 --> 00:05:47,636
Finishing the novel is not the problem.

70
00:05:47,723 --> 00:05:50,313
He can only leave when he gives up
what he can't do.

71
00:05:50,934 --> 00:05:52,984
This bus goes to the afterlife.

72
00:05:53,062 --> 00:05:55,232
You must be careful to choose
the right line.

73
00:05:55,314 --> 00:05:56,864
You can't go back.

74
00:05:57,858 --> 00:06:00,238
A few of the employees
went on the bus to the afterlife.

75
00:06:00,319 --> 00:06:02,069
We will be shorthanded for a while.

76
00:06:02,237 --> 00:06:06,117
Encourage the employees
to go to the afterlife.

77
00:06:06,408 --> 00:06:08,868
Why are you acting
like you're closing down the hotel?

78
00:06:08,952 --> 00:06:12,162
We've moved to a new place,
so we need to find a human manager.

79
00:06:12,456 --> 00:06:13,416
No need.

80
00:06:14,666 --> 00:06:15,826
We have Yu-na.

81
00:06:16,877 --> 00:06:18,877
Did they move all my things?

82
00:06:18,962 --> 00:06:21,092
Ms. Fourth Choice called a moving company

83
00:06:21,173 --> 00:06:23,553
and took care of all your things.

84
00:06:24,968 --> 00:06:27,258
Hey. You have to drive.

85
00:06:28,263 --> 00:06:31,103
I've ridden a horse,
but I have yet to drive a car.

86
00:06:31,683 --> 00:06:34,943
You haven't even learned to drive
a car for 500 years?

87
00:06:35,020 --> 00:06:38,480
You're the weird ghost
who drives around a car.

88
00:06:40,150 --> 00:06:41,240
Unbelievable.

89
00:06:44,446 --> 00:06:45,776
Darn.

90
00:06:57,376 --> 00:06:58,286
Why are you laughing?

91
00:06:58,377 --> 00:07:00,377
I find it funny
that a ghost wears a seat belt.

92
00:07:02,923 --> 00:07:05,223
I like that this is an open car.

93
00:07:05,300 --> 00:07:08,300
This is my first time
after riding in your Pony 2.

94
00:07:08,512 --> 00:07:10,472
It seems you like this pretentious thing.

95
00:07:10,889 --> 00:07:12,599
Get in, and let's take this for a spin.

96
00:07:13,475 --> 00:07:14,885
Giddy-up!

97
00:07:14,977 --> 00:07:17,437
"Giddy-up"? What a fool.

98
00:07:23,652 --> 00:07:25,952
The new place is in country side?

99
00:07:27,448 --> 00:07:30,118
This is nice. It's like going on a picnic.

100
00:07:30,659 --> 00:07:31,659
What?

101
00:07:32,327 --> 00:07:33,947
I'm talking on the phone.

102
00:07:34,037 --> 00:07:35,997
Just follow the navigation.

103
00:07:36,081 --> 00:07:37,251
Okay.

104
00:07:37,791 --> 00:07:41,301
I'd better get the driver license
to get to work.

105
00:07:41,378 --> 00:07:42,668
Just concentrate on your school.

106
00:07:42,754 --> 00:07:44,514
Summer break has started, stupid.

107
00:07:44,923 --> 00:07:46,843
And I will graduate soon.

108
00:07:47,259 --> 00:07:50,509
Her parents said they'll get me
a car if I go to college.

109
00:07:50,804 --> 00:07:53,224
I have an apartment under my name too.

110
00:07:53,765 --> 00:07:56,265
I'll get my own place
as soon as I graduate.

111
00:08:00,189 --> 00:08:03,689
It's difficult to live
with her parents, right?

112
00:08:05,611 --> 00:08:09,281
I'm just paying a very high price.

113
00:08:14,203 --> 00:08:16,713
This is strong. Do you want a sip?

114
00:08:17,748 --> 00:08:18,708
What?

115
00:08:19,333 --> 00:08:20,333
Would you?

116
00:08:20,626 --> 00:08:22,036
I'm fine.

117
00:08:39,853 --> 00:08:40,693
What's wrong?

118
00:08:46,443 --> 00:08:48,653
There's a woman in the car in front of us.

119
00:08:54,159 --> 00:08:57,039
Don't look. She can be dangerous for you.

120
00:08:58,247 --> 00:08:59,247
<i>Help me...</i>

121
00:09:00,123 --> 00:09:05,633
<i>Help me. Please...</i>

122
00:09:07,589 --> 00:09:09,299
There are many ghosts in this world.

123
00:09:09,383 --> 00:09:10,803
Don't be too concerned about them.

124
00:09:11,385 --> 00:09:14,385
I'm meant to be the manager
of Hotel del Luna.

125
00:09:14,680 --> 00:09:17,220
Let's take that ghost as our guest.

126
00:09:17,307 --> 00:09:18,137
What?

127
00:09:18,267 --> 00:09:19,267
Sir.

128
00:09:19,810 --> 00:09:21,730
A grey car just passed by us.

129
00:09:21,812 --> 00:09:22,942
Can you go after it?

130
00:09:23,021 --> 00:09:25,021
-What?
-I'll pay you extra money.

131
00:09:25,107 --> 00:09:26,977
-Can you go faster?
-Okay.

132
00:09:27,317 --> 00:09:28,817
You'll get in trouble.

133
00:09:28,902 --> 00:09:30,452
You're not even a hotel manager.

134
00:09:31,196 --> 00:09:32,196
Faster, please.

135
00:09:35,826 --> 00:09:37,406
PHARMACY

136
00:09:50,340 --> 00:09:51,930
Are you looking for Hotel del Luna?

137
00:09:52,634 --> 00:09:55,304
Did you know that the hotel moved?

138
00:09:55,929 --> 00:09:58,179
You must know where it moved.

139
00:09:58,432 --> 00:10:01,442
If I tell you, will you go find it again?

140
00:10:03,103 --> 00:10:05,313
You nearly died because of Man-wol.

141
00:10:07,107 --> 00:10:11,237
I heard you embraced that potent curse.

142
00:10:11,820 --> 00:10:16,370
If you haven't lifted that curse,
your soul is probably seriously hurt now.

143
00:10:21,413 --> 00:10:23,253
Chan-sung, let her go.

144
00:10:25,292 --> 00:10:27,172
Jang Man-wol protected me.

145
00:10:27,502 --> 00:10:28,592
I'm fine.

146
00:10:28,795 --> 00:10:31,165
Man-wol is fine thanks to you.

147
00:10:31,256 --> 00:10:32,966
You are the one who protected her.

148
00:10:33,842 --> 00:10:36,972
My sister chose the right person.

149
00:10:37,721 --> 00:10:39,721
So keep up the good work.

150
00:10:41,516 --> 00:10:44,056
Was I sent to that hotel for that purpose?

151
00:10:45,395 --> 00:10:48,065
When the terrible fate comes to her
from the past,

152
00:10:48,857 --> 00:10:50,897
am I supposed to block her from it?

153
00:10:50,984 --> 00:10:54,244
You successfully carried out your mission.
Why are you angry?

154
00:10:54,905 --> 00:10:57,365
Do you feel pity for Man-wol
you saw in your dreams?

155
00:10:58,116 --> 00:11:00,076
Yes, I do.

156
00:11:01,286 --> 00:11:04,826
I feel angry that you praise me
for not taking her side.

157
00:11:05,123 --> 00:11:07,793
She abandoned me because I got in her way.

158
00:11:08,502 --> 00:11:09,962
Are you telling me

159
00:11:10,671 --> 00:11:12,341
to keep on getting in her way?

160
00:11:12,422 --> 00:11:14,882
It's cool to take someone's side

161
00:11:15,008 --> 00:11:17,428
while getting in the way is not.

162
00:11:17,969 --> 00:11:23,729
Everyone wants
the role of embracing and consoling her.

163
00:11:24,518 --> 00:11:28,358
The shabby role of getting in the way,
holding on, and begging

164
00:11:29,272 --> 00:11:31,532
can only be done by a good person.

165
00:11:32,150 --> 00:11:33,900
Don't overestimate me.

166
00:11:33,985 --> 00:11:36,565
I don't want to take the role
that nobody wants.

167
00:11:36,655 --> 00:11:37,985
I'm not such a good person.

168
00:11:38,782 --> 00:11:41,372
Really? Then you can quit.

169
00:11:44,413 --> 00:11:45,753
Just eat this.

170
00:11:53,505 --> 00:11:54,585
What is this?

171
00:11:54,714 --> 00:11:57,974
That medicine will take away
your ability to see ghosts.

172
00:11:59,886 --> 00:12:04,716
You won't be able to see ghosts
and Hotel del Luna anymore.

173
00:12:09,146 --> 00:12:10,766
I won't be able to see all of them?

174
00:12:11,231 --> 00:12:13,531
She abandoned you too.

175
00:12:13,859 --> 00:12:17,029
I have to give you the chance
to discard her too.

176
00:12:19,364 --> 00:12:22,494
Sometimes, we can be very fair.

177
00:12:25,078 --> 00:12:27,288
I came here for a way to find her.

178
00:12:29,416 --> 00:12:31,706
But you give the way to never go back.

179
00:12:32,043 --> 00:12:34,553
The results are not given by the deities.

180
00:12:35,005 --> 00:12:36,465
It's made by humans.

181
00:12:37,591 --> 00:12:39,761
It's always the same.

182
00:12:42,846 --> 00:12:44,466
Thank you for giving me this chance.

183
00:12:45,891 --> 00:12:48,441
Wait. Are you taking it now?

184
00:12:49,227 --> 00:12:50,147
Without thinking about it?

185
00:12:50,228 --> 00:12:51,978
Did you think I wouldn't take it?

186
00:12:52,522 --> 00:12:53,732
Because I was a good person?

187
00:12:55,609 --> 00:12:57,029
I told you.

188
00:12:57,611 --> 00:13:00,451
I'm not good enough to volunteer
to take shabby roles.

189
00:13:02,532 --> 00:13:04,162
I still hesitate...

190
00:13:07,370 --> 00:13:09,080
only because she is in my heart.

191
00:13:15,962 --> 00:13:18,422
Hugging and comforting her
is nowhere enough for her.

192
00:13:19,424 --> 00:13:20,974
She's an awful woman.

193
00:13:22,427 --> 00:13:24,427
She abandoned me because I got in her way.

194
00:13:26,223 --> 00:13:28,103
Even if I went back,
she wouldn't welcome me.

195
00:13:30,852 --> 00:13:33,272
And you never know
when she'll do something dangerous again.

196
00:13:40,737 --> 00:13:43,617
I'll need to figure out
if I want to run back to her

197
00:13:44,824 --> 00:13:46,284
despite all that.

198
00:14:04,553 --> 00:14:07,143
If it's old,
it should at least look antique.

199
00:14:07,222 --> 00:14:09,522
If it's tiny, it should at least be cute.

200
00:14:10,642 --> 00:14:15,152
No matter how much I look at this,
it looks absolutely hideous.

201
00:14:15,230 --> 00:14:19,360
This was the only piece of land
we could buy with little money.

202
00:14:19,442 --> 00:14:22,702
But there is a cemetery
over the hills over there.

203
00:14:22,988 --> 00:14:25,068
The land is dark and damp, so it's great.

204
00:14:25,156 --> 00:14:28,616
And this place has great water,
so it's famous for <i>makgeolli</i> too.

205
00:14:28,702 --> 00:14:31,292
Back when you were poor and starving
as you ran Man-wol Hostel,

206
00:14:31,371 --> 00:14:34,041
you always had <i>makgeolli</i>
with radish kimchi, remember?

207
00:14:34,124 --> 00:14:35,504
That rice wine was made here.

208
00:14:35,834 --> 00:14:37,884
Stop talking about that time.

209
00:14:38,128 --> 00:14:40,168
The building looks awfully ugly enough.

210
00:14:40,255 --> 00:14:42,125
I feel like I'm as poor
as I was back then.

211
00:14:44,175 --> 00:14:47,215
Anyway, the air is really fresh.
There's no fine dust here.

212
00:14:47,596 --> 00:14:50,886
Fine dust? If it was around,
could you breathe it in?

213
00:14:51,016 --> 00:14:54,436
I can't believe a ghost is
talking about fresh water and air.

214
00:14:57,689 --> 00:15:00,399
Fine, I can just ignore the outside.

215
00:15:01,318 --> 00:15:03,568
It's all the same once I'm inside.

216
00:15:09,117 --> 00:15:10,157
Hurry up!

217
00:15:35,685 --> 00:15:38,975
The lobby looks a bit smaller,
don't you think?

218
00:15:39,940 --> 00:15:42,400
It's just your imagination.
It looks the same.

219
00:15:42,484 --> 00:15:45,824
The guests complained a lot
when we sent them off in a hurry.

220
00:15:46,029 --> 00:15:48,069
We couldn't bloom
enough flowers in the garden,

221
00:15:48,156 --> 00:15:49,906
so of course, we became poorer.

222
00:15:51,117 --> 00:15:54,197
It'll be the middle of the month,
so we'll have more guests.

223
00:15:54,287 --> 00:15:55,827
We have a great location.

224
00:15:58,249 --> 00:15:59,209
I'm thirsty.

225
00:15:59,292 --> 00:16:01,802
I'll be in the garden
looking at the Moon Tree. Bring champagne.

226
00:16:01,878 --> 00:16:05,418
Your stuff isn't here yet,
so we have no champagne.

227
00:16:06,216 --> 00:16:07,256
What?

228
00:16:08,009 --> 00:16:10,099
Why aren't they here yet?

229
00:16:10,345 --> 00:16:12,845
Are they slacking off somewhere else?

230
00:16:13,306 --> 00:16:16,266
Why don't we grab some <i>makgeolli</i>
for a change?

231
00:16:16,685 --> 00:16:18,015
Just like the old times.

232
00:16:21,523 --> 00:16:24,073
I just said I didn't want
to talk about that time.

233
00:16:25,860 --> 00:16:28,070
You forgot what I just said.

234
00:16:30,448 --> 00:16:31,698
Mr. Kim.

235
00:16:32,242 --> 00:16:34,702
You couldn't resolve your grudges
for 500 years

236
00:16:35,203 --> 00:16:37,623
maybe because you forgot what they are,

237
00:16:38,164 --> 00:16:39,754
like a goldfish.

238
00:16:40,166 --> 00:16:41,206
"A goldfish"?

239
00:16:43,253 --> 00:16:45,673
I'm a scholar who passed
the National State Exam.

240
00:16:45,755 --> 00:16:49,045
I could be an elegant crane,
not a goldfish.

241
00:16:49,134 --> 00:16:50,144
A crane?

242
00:16:52,095 --> 00:16:54,005
Both a crane and a goldfish are stupid.

243
00:17:02,022 --> 00:17:04,982
What? "Stupid"?

244
00:17:05,358 --> 00:17:08,318
I can't believe that mean and crude woman.

245
00:17:08,403 --> 00:17:09,533
Calm down.

246
00:17:10,238 --> 00:17:13,368
The outside of this hotel looks ugly,
so she's a bit ticked off.

247
00:17:13,450 --> 00:17:15,540
Man-wol only looks okay on the outside.

248
00:17:15,618 --> 00:17:17,328
She's definitely evil on the inside.

249
00:17:17,620 --> 00:17:19,080
She fired Mr. Koo,

250
00:17:19,164 --> 00:17:22,214
and she even called in a human
to do something suspicious.

251
00:17:22,292 --> 00:17:25,922
Don't you think she sacked Mr. Koo
because of what happened that day?

252
00:17:27,005 --> 00:17:29,915
She said she cut him off because she was
afraid she'd become weaker.

253
00:17:30,675 --> 00:17:33,715
I'm afraid she might do
something dangerous again.

254
00:17:33,803 --> 00:17:35,603
There is no human to stop her anymore.

255
00:17:36,347 --> 00:17:38,427
So Mr. Koo can't see ghosts anymore?

256
00:17:38,516 --> 00:17:40,266
Ms. Jang said so.

257
00:17:40,351 --> 00:17:43,941
I guess she threw
a huge crude fit at Mago.

258
00:17:47,567 --> 00:17:48,937
A goldfish?

259
00:17:58,161 --> 00:18:02,961
Hey, I thought they would
all fall off after the move,

260
00:18:03,041 --> 00:18:04,791
but they're still there.

261
00:18:06,878 --> 00:18:10,048
Did you make sure that Koo Chan-sung
can't see ghosts anymore?

262
00:18:10,131 --> 00:18:11,341
I gave him the medicine.

263
00:18:12,008 --> 00:18:14,298
If he takes it,
he won't see ghosts any longer.

264
00:18:15,845 --> 00:18:16,845
Okay.

265
00:18:18,723 --> 00:18:20,023
Good.

266
00:18:20,100 --> 00:18:24,900
You asked politely for the first time,
so I let you have your way.

267
00:18:24,979 --> 00:18:27,569
But it's up to him to decide

268
00:18:28,274 --> 00:18:29,904
to take the medicine or not.

269
00:18:30,985 --> 00:18:32,735
What would he do?

270
00:18:34,239 --> 00:18:35,489
Are you having fun?

271
00:18:36,324 --> 00:18:38,414
I might as well ask for another favor.

272
00:18:38,493 --> 00:18:40,413
Can you turn back these blue things?

273
00:18:40,495 --> 00:18:42,745
I can't do anything about those.

274
00:18:43,790 --> 00:18:46,130
That's how you feel.

275
00:18:46,209 --> 00:18:50,549
It's up to you to bloom these flowers.

276
00:18:54,676 --> 00:18:57,676
The buds look so pretty.

277
00:18:57,887 --> 00:19:02,307
I will feel so bad for them
if they can't bloom the flowers.

278
00:19:03,643 --> 00:19:06,103
Don't get your hopes up.
You won't see any flowers.

279
00:19:06,187 --> 00:19:09,017
Don't even dream
about seeing any flower here.

280
00:19:27,792 --> 00:19:29,462
Nothing changes at night either.

281
00:19:36,676 --> 00:19:38,006
<i>If you take the medicine,</i>

282
00:19:38,136 --> 00:19:41,756
<i>you won't have to see
any ghosts or Hotel del Luna anymore.</i>

283
00:19:43,474 --> 00:19:44,684
You can't stand it?

284
00:19:46,144 --> 00:19:48,194
Then run away from me, Chan-sung.

285
00:20:25,600 --> 00:20:28,270
Are you looking for a hotel?

286
00:20:29,187 --> 00:20:32,227
Hotel del Luna is not here anymore.

287
00:20:34,609 --> 00:20:36,069
I'd love to take you there,

288
00:20:36,861 --> 00:20:38,031
but I am not...

289
00:20:40,406 --> 00:20:41,816
going there anymore.

290
00:20:42,825 --> 00:20:43,905
I'm sorry.

291
00:21:19,529 --> 00:21:20,739
Are you a human?

292
00:21:22,198 --> 00:21:23,658
Do I look like a ghost?

293
00:21:24,575 --> 00:21:25,735
Who are you?

294
00:21:26,244 --> 00:21:27,334
What about you?

295
00:21:29,831 --> 00:21:31,331
I'm with the real estate office.

296
00:21:32,292 --> 00:21:35,172
This place is up for sale, so I came
to take pictures for our ads.

297
00:21:35,878 --> 00:21:36,958
For sale?

298
00:21:37,338 --> 00:21:38,968
They're selling this place?

299
00:21:40,133 --> 00:21:42,513
Yes, is there a problem?

300
00:21:42,593 --> 00:21:45,433
Yes, there are a lot of problems
in this place.

301
00:21:52,061 --> 00:21:53,151
-Yes.
-Let's see.

302
00:21:53,229 --> 00:21:55,609
-Yes.
-I have nothing to wear.

303
00:21:55,690 --> 00:21:56,940
All right.

304
00:21:57,775 --> 00:22:01,105
Ms. Jang, I got a call
from the real estate agent.

305
00:22:01,195 --> 00:22:03,105
He asked if you paid the inheritance tax.

306
00:22:03,489 --> 00:22:04,409
What tax?

307
00:22:04,490 --> 00:22:06,330
If you didn't pay that,

308
00:22:06,409 --> 00:22:08,659
there could be a problem
with the transfer tax.

309
00:22:08,745 --> 00:22:11,535
I'm not really sure what he's saying.

310
00:22:13,166 --> 00:22:14,286
How would I know?

311
00:22:15,126 --> 00:22:17,296
Should I call Mr. Koo?

312
00:22:17,628 --> 00:22:20,008
No. You can't call him.

313
00:22:21,507 --> 00:22:22,717
God...

314
00:22:23,968 --> 00:22:26,388
Is there any ghost
who would know a thing about this?

315
00:22:27,055 --> 00:22:30,135
He used to work for the biggest law firm
in Korea, Jang and Yeong.

316
00:22:30,224 --> 00:22:31,814
Then he died from overwork.

317
00:22:31,893 --> 00:22:34,813
He said he used to be
a very competent lawyer.

318
00:22:34,896 --> 00:22:35,766
Really?

319
00:22:37,398 --> 00:22:40,108
Mr. Jang and Yeong. So what's the problem?

320
00:22:40,193 --> 00:22:42,453
What's the deal with the inheritance tax?

321
00:22:42,528 --> 00:22:44,948
The late Mr. No Jun-seok

322
00:22:45,031 --> 00:22:47,031
left the building to you, Ms. Jang.

323
00:22:47,116 --> 00:22:50,236
And he prepared all the paperwork
for you to pay the inheritance tax.

324
00:22:50,745 --> 00:22:51,905
You can just pay it now.

325
00:22:52,538 --> 00:22:53,708
With what?

326
00:22:53,790 --> 00:22:55,670
Didn't you prepare the money?

327
00:22:55,750 --> 00:22:58,090
No idea.
The guy who prepared that isn't here.

328
00:22:58,169 --> 00:23:00,339
I have no idea if he prepared it at all.

329
00:23:03,966 --> 00:23:05,756
If you sell your land to pay the taxes...

330
00:23:05,843 --> 00:23:06,973
The inheritance tax,

331
00:23:08,262 --> 00:23:10,182
the mortgage,

332
00:23:10,431 --> 00:23:12,061
and the transfer tax...

333
00:23:16,562 --> 00:23:18,482
There won't be much money left.

334
00:23:19,107 --> 00:23:20,777
Why not? That's impossible.

335
00:23:20,858 --> 00:23:22,438
I was told that land is very expensive.

336
00:23:22,527 --> 00:23:24,777
Why wouldn't there be much money left?

337
00:23:25,613 --> 00:23:27,373
That's how it works with taxes.

338
00:23:27,907 --> 00:23:31,327
You should just pay the inheritance tax
and hold onto the land.

339
00:23:38,835 --> 00:23:41,875
Mr. Jang and Yeong.

340
00:23:42,171 --> 00:23:44,131
What are you doing?
You have to take care of this.

341
00:23:46,050 --> 00:23:49,390
Mr. Jang and Yeong.

342
00:23:49,470 --> 00:23:52,520
Because he died from overwork,

343
00:23:52,598 --> 00:23:55,478
he faints if he reads anything
for more than five minutes.

344
00:24:00,606 --> 00:24:04,106
What kind of ridiculous situation is this?

345
00:24:05,153 --> 00:24:06,323
Darn it.

346
00:24:06,779 --> 00:24:09,029
Sure thing. Please give me a call, then.

347
00:24:09,323 --> 00:24:12,333
By the way, how did you know
about the inheritance tax?

348
00:24:12,410 --> 00:24:13,870
I came to see the building,

349
00:24:14,620 --> 00:24:16,790
and I ran into someone
by the name of Koo Chan-sung.

350
00:24:18,541 --> 00:24:20,041
He's here with me right now.

351
00:24:22,086 --> 00:24:23,126
He's there?

352
00:24:26,090 --> 00:24:27,590
Could I speak to him?

353
00:24:27,758 --> 00:24:30,138
God, it's all Greek to me.

354
00:24:30,678 --> 00:24:32,558
Damn it!

355
00:24:32,889 --> 00:24:35,139
Ms. Jang,
why don't you speak to him directly?

356
00:24:35,224 --> 00:24:37,524
I have no clue what he's talking about.

357
00:24:37,810 --> 00:24:39,270
And do you think I'd know?

358
00:24:43,649 --> 00:24:46,359
Hey, Mr. Realtor.
Tell me, and make it easy and simple.

359
00:24:46,611 --> 00:24:48,071
How much will I get out of it?

360
00:24:49,155 --> 00:24:50,655
Don't try to swindle me.

361
00:24:50,740 --> 00:24:54,240
I have a talented employee
who got his MBA from Harvard.

362
00:24:54,744 --> 00:24:55,874
<i>But you fired him.</i>

363
00:24:58,956 --> 00:24:59,826
Koo Chan-sung?

364
00:24:59,916 --> 00:25:02,746
You don't know a thing about the taxes,
inheritance or transfer one, do you?

365
00:25:02,960 --> 00:25:05,090
Why did you fire your talented employee?

366
00:25:07,423 --> 00:25:08,803
Why are you over there?

367
00:25:08,883 --> 00:25:11,183
Did you get hired by a realtor?

368
00:25:11,260 --> 00:25:13,680
I came here because I was flustered
after getting fired overnight.

369
00:25:13,971 --> 00:25:15,391
You must be regretting firing me.

370
00:25:19,685 --> 00:25:21,805
If you just ask me to come back,

371
00:25:22,188 --> 00:25:23,728
I can be there immediately.

372
00:25:28,527 --> 00:25:30,277
Tell this to the realtor.

373
00:25:30,404 --> 00:25:32,284
He should kick out anyone
that's unrelated,

374
00:25:32,448 --> 00:25:34,278
and lock up the place well.

375
00:25:37,954 --> 00:25:40,214
<i>Okay. I got it.</i>

376
00:25:50,174 --> 00:25:53,264
Was Mr. Koo over there?

377
00:25:55,054 --> 00:25:57,474
He must have been searching for us
all night long.

378
00:25:57,556 --> 00:25:59,056
MANAGER KOO CHAN-SUNG

379
00:25:59,141 --> 00:26:01,941
If he calls back,
tell him to call us when he's dead.

380
00:26:05,106 --> 00:26:06,816
Right, Hyeon-jung and Yu-na!

381
00:26:07,942 --> 00:26:09,862
Check if they're on their way.

382
00:26:10,528 --> 00:26:11,528
Yes, ma'am.

383
00:26:40,016 --> 00:26:42,346
If you don't like those, wear these.

384
00:26:42,893 --> 00:26:45,563
No, they're not my type.

385
00:26:53,738 --> 00:26:56,198
Wear your tacky poop colored shoes...

386
00:26:58,659 --> 00:27:01,289
and go work at a normal hotel.

387
00:27:02,038 --> 00:27:03,328
Okay, Chan-sung?

388
00:27:31,650 --> 00:27:34,400
I have to lock up, so please leave.

389
00:28:03,974 --> 00:28:06,734
Hey, where are we?

390
00:28:07,853 --> 00:28:10,903
We got lost while chasing the other car.

391
00:28:12,525 --> 00:28:14,395
Even the GPS can't find this road.

392
00:28:15,903 --> 00:28:18,613
Where on earth are we?

393
00:28:24,829 --> 00:28:27,159
What's the matter?

394
00:28:29,166 --> 00:28:30,576
I saw someone on the road.

395
00:28:32,253 --> 00:28:33,633
I don't see anyone.

396
00:28:35,798 --> 00:28:36,878
There.

397
00:28:43,764 --> 00:28:44,774
Gosh.

398
00:28:45,433 --> 00:28:46,773
I'm sorry.

399
00:28:47,435 --> 00:28:49,015
The car is not cooperating.

400
00:28:50,187 --> 00:28:51,647
No.

401
00:28:52,106 --> 00:28:53,816
I think we came to the right place.

402
00:28:56,110 --> 00:28:58,900
I'll go out to a bigger road
to meet with the insurance agent.

403
00:28:59,447 --> 00:29:00,697
See you later.

404
00:29:01,115 --> 00:29:02,695
Darn it.

405
00:29:06,078 --> 00:29:07,578
It was a man just now, wasn't it?

406
00:29:07,997 --> 00:29:10,037
The ghost in the car earlier was a woman.

407
00:29:10,833 --> 00:29:11,793
Let's go and see.

408
00:29:11,876 --> 00:29:12,786
Yu-na.

409
00:29:13,669 --> 00:29:15,129
I think it'll be too dangerous.

410
00:29:15,212 --> 00:29:18,012
You're a ghost too.
I used to be one as well.

411
00:29:18,090 --> 00:29:20,430
It's not that. Did you see the driver

412
00:29:20,676 --> 00:29:21,926
of that car?

413
00:29:24,430 --> 00:29:27,930
<i>It was a young man wearing sunglasses.</i>

414
00:29:28,517 --> 00:29:31,307
There was a ghost in that man's car,

415
00:29:31,395 --> 00:29:33,855
and when we chased after the car,
we found another ghost.

416
00:29:34,648 --> 00:29:35,608
It feels a little...

417
00:29:35,691 --> 00:29:39,821
Do you think they were killed by that man?

418
00:29:39,904 --> 00:29:42,114
Humans can be more dangerous than ghosts.

419
00:29:42,198 --> 00:29:45,238
If they died wrongfully,
I can't just leave.

420
00:29:46,452 --> 00:29:48,452
I died wrongfully too.

421
00:29:50,664 --> 00:29:51,964
I'll be careful.

422
00:29:53,209 --> 00:29:56,499
Then promise me. You have to run back
to our car if you see a human.

423
00:29:56,670 --> 00:29:58,210
-Okay?
-Okay.

424
00:29:59,465 --> 00:30:03,335
By the way, it's usually people
who fear ghosts.

425
00:30:03,427 --> 00:30:05,507
But we ghosts are scared of humans.

426
00:30:06,055 --> 00:30:07,095
You're right.

427
00:30:07,932 --> 00:30:10,142
He looked like an ordinary person.

428
00:30:48,764 --> 00:30:51,184
This is our signature cocktail

429
00:30:51,267 --> 00:30:53,097
the guests at the bar like the most.

430
00:30:56,814 --> 00:30:58,364
Did you make this?

431
00:30:58,482 --> 00:30:59,482
I did.

432
00:31:00,109 --> 00:31:02,489
They dream of life here while being drunk.

433
00:31:02,570 --> 00:31:04,530
These might be
the last drops of their tears

434
00:31:04,613 --> 00:31:06,533
while they dream their lives away.

435
00:31:08,534 --> 00:31:11,504
Why would you name it in English
when you were a Confucian scholar?

436
00:31:11,579 --> 00:31:13,159
You're trying too hard to look cool.

437
00:31:13,247 --> 00:31:15,167
I don't think someone who named this hotel

438
00:31:15,249 --> 00:31:17,959
with a pretentious name
like "Hotel del Luna" can criticize.

439
00:31:21,630 --> 00:31:25,720
As I expected, cocktails made by ghosts
are so disgusting.

440
00:31:28,012 --> 00:31:30,062
I heard <i>makgeolli</i> is famous
in this village.

441
00:31:30,139 --> 00:31:31,519
Don't you have any?

442
00:31:32,391 --> 00:31:34,891
You're the one who told me
to never bring it up.

443
00:31:34,977 --> 00:31:35,937
Did you forget?

444
00:31:36,020 --> 00:31:38,770
Since when were you so obedient
to my orders?

445
00:31:40,357 --> 00:31:43,437
I lost my appetite
because of this cocktail.

446
00:31:48,115 --> 00:31:50,365
I know she's bored but can't go shopping.

447
00:31:50,451 --> 00:31:52,451
But why is she taking it out on me?

448
00:31:58,042 --> 00:31:59,752
It's delicious to me.

449
00:32:01,420 --> 00:32:03,380
MAIN BUILDING

450
00:32:06,383 --> 00:32:07,383
BORAM <i>MAKGEOLLI</i>

451
00:32:17,519 --> 00:32:18,519
It's good.

452
00:32:34,411 --> 00:32:35,501
What's this?

453
00:32:41,502 --> 00:32:43,422
Who drank all this?

454
00:32:53,472 --> 00:32:56,182
This village makes amazing <i>makgeolli</i>.

455
00:32:57,601 --> 00:33:00,311
I wonder if there's anything to snack on.

456
00:33:00,813 --> 00:33:02,693
Is there a radish field around here?

457
00:33:03,315 --> 00:33:06,435
This will taste great with some radish.

458
00:33:07,403 --> 00:33:12,833
<i>Let's see
Where's the radish field?</i>

459
00:33:22,292 --> 00:33:25,672
No wonder the <i>makgeolli</i> tasted so nice.

460
00:33:46,817 --> 00:33:49,897
Are you the big tree
beyond the hill over there?

461
00:33:51,113 --> 00:33:52,413
Yes.

462
00:33:53,615 --> 00:33:55,445
You've built a very nice house.

463
00:33:56,452 --> 00:33:58,452
That place must be
the Guest House of the Moon,

464
00:33:58,537 --> 00:33:59,657
where souls come to rest.

465
00:34:00,080 --> 00:34:01,120
Yes.

466
00:34:01,582 --> 00:34:03,582
And I'm the owner.

467
00:34:04,543 --> 00:34:06,843
I'm the Guardian of the Well
of this village.

468
00:34:07,963 --> 00:34:10,473
This village has a deity
who protects its well.

469
00:34:10,549 --> 00:34:12,299
No wonder the water tasted so nice here.

470
00:34:12,593 --> 00:34:15,723
I got to taste great <i>makgeolli</i>
thanks to you.

471
00:34:35,741 --> 00:34:38,201
You got fired?
Did you get fired because of me?

472
00:34:38,285 --> 00:34:39,695
What in the world did you do

473
00:34:39,787 --> 00:34:41,827
to cause so much trouble
at Chan-sung's hotel?

474
00:34:43,082 --> 00:34:44,372
I can't remember.

475
00:34:44,792 --> 00:34:46,712
I remember feeling happy
because the hotel was so nice.

476
00:34:46,794 --> 00:34:48,634
But I can't remember
anything else after that.

477
00:34:49,254 --> 00:34:50,594
And when I woke up,

478
00:34:51,090 --> 00:34:52,880
I was drunk in a cab.

479
00:34:53,383 --> 00:34:54,683
I can't remember if I drank.

480
00:34:54,968 --> 00:34:56,928
You probably did. You love alcohol.

481
00:34:57,012 --> 00:34:58,722
You probably got drunk and caused trouble.

482
00:34:58,806 --> 00:35:00,846
That's your thing.
I saw it a couple times.

483
00:35:00,933 --> 00:35:02,233
It wasn't because of Mi-ra.

484
00:35:03,102 --> 00:35:04,272
I just got fired

485
00:35:05,562 --> 00:35:07,402
because she thought I was a nuisance.

486
00:35:10,859 --> 00:35:12,609
I should find a way to go back.

487
00:35:18,367 --> 00:35:20,367
I guess Man-wol dumped Chan-sung.

488
00:35:20,452 --> 00:35:22,832
But it's not like
they went out with each other.

489
00:35:23,163 --> 00:35:24,873
Chan-sung liked her.

490
00:35:25,374 --> 00:35:28,544
Man-wol left him with an expensive
painting, so he'd leave her alone.

491
00:35:28,627 --> 00:35:31,337
I've seen my yacht club members
do the same thing.

492
00:35:31,463 --> 00:35:33,673
I never thought she would do that.
She's so mean.

493
00:35:33,757 --> 00:35:37,217
Are you saying that huge painting
of the mountain

494
00:35:37,427 --> 00:35:39,297
is worth a lot of money?

495
00:35:39,388 --> 00:35:42,098
Did she really have to give him
a painting of Baekdu Mountain?

496
00:35:42,182 --> 00:35:45,562
He's going to feel sad every time
he listens to the national anthem.

497
00:36:03,073 --> 00:36:04,073
Sir.

498
00:36:04,574 --> 00:36:08,294
As I thought, you have the ability
to see dead people.

499
00:36:11,206 --> 00:36:13,826
I saw on the news that you passed away.

500
00:36:14,209 --> 00:36:16,039
I'm sorry I didn't get to visit you.

501
00:36:17,545 --> 00:36:21,835
I wanted to see this painting
one last time before I leave.

502
00:36:22,926 --> 00:36:25,256
Is the tiger inside this painting?

503
00:36:25,345 --> 00:36:27,555
The tiger rested well
at the hotel I used to work at,

504
00:36:28,223 --> 00:36:29,433
and left for the afterlife.

505
00:36:29,933 --> 00:36:30,983
A hotel?

506
00:36:31,184 --> 00:36:35,064
Only dead people like you
can visit that hotel.

507
00:36:35,146 --> 00:36:38,526
You're working
at a very interesting hotel.

508
00:36:38,608 --> 00:36:40,778
I'd like to go there too.

509
00:36:42,404 --> 00:36:43,664
You can go there.

510
00:36:44,030 --> 00:36:46,490
You'll be able to see it very well.

511
00:36:52,163 --> 00:36:53,163
Are you going somewhere?

512
00:36:53,915 --> 00:36:55,535
Yes, I'm going to the hotel.

513
00:36:55,959 --> 00:36:57,419
I thought you can't go there anymore.

514
00:36:57,502 --> 00:36:58,712
I found a way.

515
00:37:00,588 --> 00:37:01,588
Let's go.

516
00:37:08,596 --> 00:37:09,926
Chan-sung has a lot of pride.

517
00:37:10,014 --> 00:37:12,064
I wonder if he's going there to beg her.

518
00:37:12,600 --> 00:37:13,560
That's not like him.

519
00:37:14,144 --> 00:37:16,064
You're really weird too.

520
00:37:16,938 --> 00:37:18,058
Why aren't you stopping him?

521
00:37:18,148 --> 00:37:20,188
You came all the way here
because of Chan-sung.

522
00:37:20,275 --> 00:37:23,355
You kept interrupting their date.
Why are you just letting him go?

523
00:37:23,445 --> 00:37:24,485
I just

524
00:37:24,988 --> 00:37:26,358
decided to give up.

525
00:37:26,531 --> 00:37:27,531
What?

526
00:37:27,615 --> 00:37:30,285
I wanted to make
Chan-sung come back to me,

527
00:37:30,577 --> 00:37:33,497
but I figured I should just give up

528
00:37:33,955 --> 00:37:35,615
once I met Jang Man-wol.

529
00:37:35,707 --> 00:37:38,707
Why? Because she's rich?
Or because she's pretty?

530
00:37:38,793 --> 00:37:41,383
I make good money, and I'm pretty too.

531
00:37:42,756 --> 00:37:46,926
But I have a feeling
that I'm no match for her.

532
00:37:48,178 --> 00:37:49,758
I wonder what's wrong with me.

533
00:37:49,846 --> 00:37:51,886
Do I owe her something
in my previous life?

534
00:37:52,182 --> 00:37:54,102
That's possible.

535
00:37:54,768 --> 00:37:56,688
You owe a lot of money
in this life as well.

536
00:37:58,480 --> 00:37:59,810
I'm going to pay everything back.

537
00:38:00,106 --> 00:38:03,776
Plus, I hold our alumni reunion
at your restaurant.

538
00:38:04,611 --> 00:38:06,151
I should check the group chat.

539
00:38:08,823 --> 00:38:10,333
I'm also a member of that group chat,

540
00:38:10,408 --> 00:38:11,988
and I'm the one who gathers everyone.

541
00:38:12,076 --> 00:38:14,656
Why is she acting like
she does all the work?

542
00:38:29,677 --> 00:38:31,097
Are you coming back from somewhere?

543
00:38:31,304 --> 00:38:32,144
Yes.

544
00:38:33,306 --> 00:38:35,726
Where's all my stuff?
They're not here yet?

545
00:38:35,809 --> 00:38:39,189
Hyeon-jung and the intern
ran into ghosts on their way here.

546
00:38:39,270 --> 00:38:41,060
They wish to bring them here as a guest.

547
00:38:42,190 --> 00:38:44,150
I knew it.

548
00:38:44,234 --> 00:38:45,824
They got sidetracked.

549
00:38:46,152 --> 00:38:49,452
Hyeon-jung must've learned that
from Mr. Koo.

550
00:38:51,574 --> 00:38:54,664
After what happened
to our guest in Room 13,

551
00:38:54,744 --> 00:38:58,294
Mr. Koo could never be indifferent
to wandering ghosts.

552
00:39:01,876 --> 00:39:02,996
Yes, you're right.

553
00:39:13,304 --> 00:39:15,604
I brought her from the public restroom.

554
00:39:15,723 --> 00:39:18,893
Do you want the red toilet paper
or the blue toilet paper?

555
00:39:18,977 --> 00:39:21,977
Do you want the red toilet paper
or the blue toilet paper?

556
00:39:22,063 --> 00:39:24,483
Gosh, how long have you been saying that?

557
00:39:24,691 --> 00:39:26,361
I think I heard it when I was young.

558
00:39:28,236 --> 00:39:30,406
Come with me. You should take some rest.

559
00:39:30,989 --> 00:39:34,579
Do you want the red toilet paper
or the blue toilet paper?

560
00:39:41,666 --> 00:39:43,916
He was hovering by the crosswalk,
so I brought him here.

561
00:39:45,211 --> 00:39:47,801
It's not that way. It's this way.

562
00:40:19,888 --> 00:40:21,308
He's a coward

563
00:40:22,223 --> 00:40:24,103
with such a soft heart.

564
00:40:43,286 --> 00:40:44,406
Chan-sung?

565
00:40:58,259 --> 00:41:01,049
The late chairman came to my house.

566
00:41:01,137 --> 00:41:02,557
So I brought him here.

567
00:41:03,139 --> 00:41:07,059
He told me that this hotel is
much more magnificent than mine.

568
00:41:07,185 --> 00:41:08,435
So I thought I'd pay a visit.

569
00:41:11,648 --> 00:41:13,478
This place is amazing.

570
00:41:18,988 --> 00:41:22,278
You're here as our guest, so we'll do
our best to make you feel comfortable.

571
00:41:22,867 --> 00:41:23,907
Ms. Choe.

572
00:41:24,953 --> 00:41:26,963
Let me take you to your room.

573
00:41:27,413 --> 00:41:28,463
Please follow me.

574
00:41:35,213 --> 00:41:36,463
Chan-sung.

575
00:41:37,632 --> 00:41:39,592
You really played it smart.

576
00:41:39,676 --> 00:41:42,136
You coaxed him to find our hotel
and followed him here?

577
00:41:42,220 --> 00:41:43,600
I did follow him here.

578
00:41:44,222 --> 00:41:46,102
But I didn't coax him to find here.

579
00:41:46,766 --> 00:41:48,766
I met him for another reason.

580
00:41:48,851 --> 00:41:49,891
What reason?

581
00:41:50,061 --> 00:41:51,311
Mr. Koo.

582
00:41:53,106 --> 00:41:55,976
Call my secretary to settle things
regarding the painting.

583
00:41:56,317 --> 00:41:59,107
They're planning to make
a memorial hall for me.

584
00:41:59,237 --> 00:42:01,197
They'll pay you a good price for it.

585
00:42:04,117 --> 00:42:05,117
Yes, sir.

586
00:42:10,039 --> 00:42:11,119
What painting?

587
00:42:11,207 --> 00:42:13,537
The painting of the Baekdu Mountain
that you gave me

588
00:42:13,626 --> 00:42:15,206
because you thought it took up space.

589
00:42:15,503 --> 00:42:16,553
You told me

590
00:42:17,005 --> 00:42:19,465
that you couldn't sell it
for even a quarter of the price.

591
00:42:19,549 --> 00:42:20,839
I just didn't sell it,

592
00:42:21,175 --> 00:42:24,045
since the price of it would get higher
after the Chairman dies.

593
00:42:24,595 --> 00:42:27,175
You should've told me then!
Then I wouldn't have--

594
00:42:27,265 --> 00:42:28,345
No, you wouldn't.

595
00:42:30,351 --> 00:42:32,101
Thanks for the severance pay.

596
00:42:34,939 --> 00:42:36,229
You fraud.

597
00:42:36,315 --> 00:42:37,475
I didn't lie to you.

598
00:42:38,151 --> 00:42:41,361
I didn't expect you to abandon

599
00:42:41,612 --> 00:42:42,862
both the painting...

600
00:42:45,283 --> 00:42:46,333
and me.

601
00:42:55,168 --> 00:42:56,838
-Let's split the money.
-I won't.

602
00:42:56,919 --> 00:42:59,919
You greedy fraud from Harvard!

603
00:43:04,469 --> 00:43:06,549
Okay, give me a quarter of the price.

604
00:43:06,637 --> 00:43:07,637
No.

605
00:43:08,347 --> 00:43:10,677
I'm not selling it
unless I get the full price to myself.

606
00:43:12,351 --> 00:43:15,521
You had no idea how expensive it was
when you gave it to me.

607
00:43:20,568 --> 00:43:22,028
You must have gone broke.

608
00:43:22,987 --> 00:43:24,197
You're drinking <i>makgeolli</i>.

609
00:43:24,322 --> 00:43:26,372
Whatever. Get out!

610
00:43:37,126 --> 00:43:39,706
I'll sell the painting
and bring some cash.

611
00:43:39,879 --> 00:43:41,919
Money is the best way to get her.

612
00:43:58,731 --> 00:43:59,981
Welcome.

613
00:44:01,234 --> 00:44:04,074
May I come in?

614
00:44:04,487 --> 00:44:05,527
Of course.

615
00:44:08,533 --> 00:44:09,533
Please come in.

616
00:44:11,869 --> 00:44:13,329
What a friendly man.

617
00:44:14,330 --> 00:44:15,370
Thank you.

618
00:45:11,304 --> 00:45:15,984
Rich families must have
secret funds that nobody knows about.

619
00:45:16,142 --> 00:45:17,812
Since they're filthy rich,

620
00:45:17,894 --> 00:45:20,694
they often have money
that they forget to tell people about

621
00:45:20,771 --> 00:45:22,111
before they die.

622
00:45:23,399 --> 00:45:26,069
Perhaps it could be a Swiss bank account,

623
00:45:26,652 --> 00:45:29,322
a secret account in Virgin Islands,

624
00:45:30,615 --> 00:45:34,285
or maybe just a safe filled with money

625
00:45:34,368 --> 00:45:37,708
buried in a sunflower field
or something. You got any?

626
00:45:40,291 --> 00:45:41,581
Well, I don't know.

627
00:45:44,921 --> 00:45:47,921
Take your time, and think carefully.

628
00:46:23,876 --> 00:46:25,086
This is water.

629
00:46:27,588 --> 00:46:29,258
Ms. Jang, we're in trouble.

630
00:46:29,840 --> 00:46:33,680
Something that shouldn't be
inside the hotel is in here now.

631
00:46:48,859 --> 00:46:51,029
The hotel is flooded with water.

632
00:46:51,445 --> 00:46:53,155
What's come in here?

633
00:46:55,074 --> 00:46:56,994
It passed by me when it came in.

634
00:46:57,118 --> 00:46:58,738
It wasn't a soul of a human.

635
00:46:59,704 --> 00:47:02,754
It was a deity disguised in the body
of a young man.

636
00:47:03,958 --> 00:47:05,078
A deity?

637
00:47:11,841 --> 00:47:12,881
I know what it is.

638
00:47:13,342 --> 00:47:14,932
How did it get in here?

639
00:47:16,012 --> 00:47:18,642
This area is controlled by Mago.

640
00:47:19,265 --> 00:47:21,925
Other deities can't get inside
without permission.

641
00:47:35,031 --> 00:47:36,871
Perhaps someone let it in.

642
00:47:44,165 --> 00:47:46,325
I honestly thought it was
just a regular guest.

643
00:47:46,459 --> 00:47:47,839
Who is it anyway?

644
00:47:47,918 --> 00:47:49,998
It's the deity that takes care
of the well in this village.

645
00:47:50,296 --> 00:47:51,416
A deity?

646
00:47:51,589 --> 00:47:54,549
You mean like the mountain deity
in the folktale about golden axes?

647
00:47:54,633 --> 00:47:57,803
Exactly. He is the Guardian of the Well.

648
00:47:59,055 --> 00:48:01,055
How could you let such a thing in?

649
00:48:01,724 --> 00:48:04,064
I had no idea.
I've never seen someone like that,

650
00:48:04,143 --> 00:48:06,773
how was I supposed to know the difference?

651
00:48:09,732 --> 00:48:11,732
It's because our hotel has just moved

652
00:48:12,151 --> 00:48:14,651
and because Hyeon-jung is absent.

653
00:48:15,529 --> 00:48:17,029
It's all your fault!

654
00:48:18,032 --> 00:48:20,492
Yes, let's just say
that everything is my fault.

655
00:48:20,743 --> 00:48:23,833
What should we do now?
Do I just tell him to get out?

656
00:48:25,081 --> 00:48:26,751
You can't chase a deity away.

657
00:48:28,167 --> 00:48:30,957
We can't tell him to get out
since we're the ones that let him in.

658
00:48:32,379 --> 00:48:34,419
We have no choice but to serve him.

659
00:48:34,507 --> 00:48:37,087
Why did the deity leave his well
and come all the way here?

660
00:48:37,176 --> 00:48:39,256
Something must've bothered him.

661
00:48:41,430 --> 00:48:45,430
It must be a disaster out there,
without the deity in his place.

662
00:48:46,477 --> 00:48:48,097
Goodness.

663
00:48:49,647 --> 00:48:52,527
It's going to get busy from next month.
Keep up the good work.

664
00:48:52,608 --> 00:48:53,728
-Yes, sir.
-Yes, sir.

665
00:48:53,818 --> 00:48:54,988
It's quite hot outside today.

666
00:48:55,069 --> 00:48:57,239
Boss, the water taps aren't working.

667
00:48:57,321 --> 00:48:59,531
What? What do you mean?

668
00:49:02,451 --> 00:49:04,701
-Why isn't water coming out?
-Exactly.

669
00:49:04,870 --> 00:49:06,210
This is bad.

670
00:49:13,504 --> 00:49:14,804
The well is dry.

671
00:49:14,880 --> 00:49:16,170
What do we do?

672
00:49:16,799 --> 00:49:19,389
-What's happened?
-How can this happen?

673
00:49:19,468 --> 00:49:20,638
What's going on?

674
00:49:20,719 --> 00:49:23,099
-It's all dry.
-How can this happen?

675
00:49:41,198 --> 00:49:43,448
The well is the main water source
of the area,

676
00:49:43,534 --> 00:49:45,454
so if it dries up, so will the <i>makgeolli</i>.

677
00:49:46,579 --> 00:49:48,249
Why is my hotel flooded with the water

678
00:49:48,330 --> 00:49:50,500
that should've been used to make
the <i>makgeolli</i>?

679
00:49:51,333 --> 00:49:54,253
My beautifully-painted walls
will all get wet.

680
00:49:55,337 --> 00:49:57,007
My walls are going to get mold.

681
00:49:58,007 --> 00:49:59,677
They might even rot.

682
00:50:00,926 --> 00:50:04,506
Ms. Choe is checking to see
what room he's staying in.

683
00:50:04,597 --> 00:50:05,847
We can't kick him out,

684
00:50:05,931 --> 00:50:08,811
but maybe we can convince him
to walk out on his own.

685
00:50:09,268 --> 00:50:10,898
I'll go talk to him when we find him.

686
00:50:10,978 --> 00:50:13,358
Do you have any idea
how scary angry deities are?

687
00:50:13,439 --> 00:50:16,399
Back in the days, we even had to give
human sacrifices to calm them.

688
00:50:16,483 --> 00:50:17,993
Maybe deities didn't ask humans
to do that,

689
00:50:18,152 --> 00:50:20,532
but people just did that in fear.

690
00:50:21,572 --> 00:50:23,822
Mr. Koo, why are you back here?

691
00:50:23,908 --> 00:50:25,528
Didn't you meet Mago?

692
00:50:30,497 --> 00:50:31,617
I found him.

693
00:50:32,750 --> 00:50:34,670
He's staying in a room
on the eighth floor.

694
00:50:34,752 --> 00:50:37,632
Prepare drinks and some food
to make him feel better.

695
00:50:37,713 --> 00:50:39,473
He said that he doesn't need anything

696
00:50:39,548 --> 00:50:40,968
except for one.

697
00:50:42,134 --> 00:50:44,804
He wants Mr. Koo to come up to his room.

698
00:50:46,513 --> 00:50:47,893
Why does he want Chan-sung?

699
00:50:48,474 --> 00:50:49,734
I'm the owner. I'm going up.

700
00:50:49,808 --> 00:50:53,598
No, he wants a living human.

701
00:50:57,316 --> 00:50:59,816
Is he actually expecting
a human sacrifice?

702
00:51:13,249 --> 00:51:14,419
Where are you going?

703
00:51:14,500 --> 00:51:15,830
To catch humans.

704
00:51:15,918 --> 00:51:16,918
What?

705
00:51:18,420 --> 00:51:21,010
He's probably angry
because of the humans in this village.

706
00:51:21,090 --> 00:51:23,840
I'll catch a few of them
and make them apologize to him.

707
00:51:27,638 --> 00:51:29,768
-It's too dangerous.
-I don't care.

708
00:51:30,599 --> 00:51:31,679
I won't send you in there.

709
00:51:40,484 --> 00:51:42,194
I opened the door for him.

710
00:51:42,278 --> 00:51:45,278
He thanked me.
I'm sure he wouldn't harm me.

711
00:51:47,658 --> 00:51:48,778
I'll go see him.

712
00:51:56,917 --> 00:51:58,587
There's something I wanted to ask you.

713
00:51:59,169 --> 00:52:00,339
I'll just ask.

714
00:52:00,796 --> 00:52:02,916
Don't people usually ask, "May I ask?"

715
00:52:03,716 --> 00:52:07,296
Who's the old woman
that we saw at the hospital the other day?

716
00:52:15,352 --> 00:52:16,772
<i>You knew her, didn't you?</i>

717
00:52:18,897 --> 00:52:21,477
Yes, she's my younger sister.

718
00:52:21,775 --> 00:52:25,145
What? Younger sister? That old woman?

719
00:52:25,529 --> 00:52:28,569
She may have grown old,
but she's still my cute sister

720
00:52:28,657 --> 00:52:30,697
who always smiled when she called me.

721
00:52:32,119 --> 00:52:33,369
"Your cute sister"?

722
00:52:33,787 --> 00:52:34,997
What's her name?

723
00:52:35,080 --> 00:52:38,790
Hyeon-mi.
Ji Hyeon-jung's sister, Ji Hyeon-mi.

724
00:52:39,668 --> 00:52:41,088
Hyeon-mi.

725
00:52:41,378 --> 00:52:45,918
I should visit her
and ask if she remembers Hyeon-jung.

726
00:52:46,425 --> 00:52:47,545
No.

727
00:52:48,260 --> 00:52:49,390
Don't do it.

728
00:52:49,470 --> 00:52:52,060
Don't visit her. I mean it.

729
00:52:53,223 --> 00:52:57,103
Hey, do you think I'm someone
who would say something bad to a sister

730
00:52:57,186 --> 00:52:58,226
of someone I like?

731
00:53:06,570 --> 00:53:08,780
Darn it, this is awful.

732
00:53:09,782 --> 00:53:11,992
Why did I say that
in this mountain full of ghosts?

733
00:53:12,076 --> 00:53:13,076
I'm so stupid!

734
00:53:14,370 --> 00:53:15,540
Be careful.

735
00:53:16,663 --> 00:53:17,663
Are you okay?

736
00:53:39,853 --> 00:53:41,153
Hyeon-jung.

737
00:53:43,273 --> 00:53:44,443
I found him.

738
00:53:45,484 --> 00:53:47,444
-Yu-na.
-Yes?

739
00:53:48,779 --> 00:53:50,989
I don't think he's alone.

740
00:53:51,824 --> 00:53:52,704
Look.

741
00:54:16,598 --> 00:54:18,178
The fog is really thick.

742
00:54:21,353 --> 00:54:23,613
Just in case you just wanted
to look bold earlier,

743
00:54:23,689 --> 00:54:24,859
I'll stop you this once.

744
00:54:25,607 --> 00:54:27,987
Chan-sung, do not go inside. Go back.

745
00:54:29,111 --> 00:54:32,031
I look kind of cool
now that you're trying to stop me.

746
00:54:32,114 --> 00:54:35,334
Forget it. You're a coward.
You can hardly look cool.

747
00:54:35,784 --> 00:54:36,914
Just run away.

748
00:54:36,994 --> 00:54:39,164
I did you a favor and let you go.
Why did you come back?

749
00:54:39,788 --> 00:54:41,418
You gave me your time again.

750
00:54:42,291 --> 00:54:45,341
It was one, two, three.

751
00:54:46,712 --> 00:54:47,802
Three seconds.

752
00:54:51,550 --> 00:54:53,970
If you just ask me to come back,

753
00:54:54,052 --> 00:54:55,802
I can be there immediately.

754
00:55:09,151 --> 00:55:12,531
<i>For a short moment,
you wanted me to return.</i>

755
00:55:12,946 --> 00:55:14,316
This time, for three seconds.

756
00:55:19,286 --> 00:55:20,906
How could I not come?

757
00:55:26,210 --> 00:55:28,090
Do not smile. You're making me angry.

758
00:55:29,713 --> 00:55:31,923
You aren't angry. You're worried.

759
00:55:35,719 --> 00:55:36,889
Don't worry.

760
00:55:38,013 --> 00:55:40,773
In my experience, I could tell
that the deities like me.

761
00:55:40,849 --> 00:55:42,139
It must be because I'm weak-hearted.

762
00:56:47,916 --> 00:56:49,036
Chan-sung!

763
00:57:12,232 --> 00:57:13,152
Chan-sung.

764
00:57:13,900 --> 00:57:15,860
Answer me. Chan-sung!

765
00:57:51,480 --> 00:57:53,320
Goodness, what is this?

766
00:58:00,197 --> 00:58:01,447
Are you here?

767
00:58:02,908 --> 00:58:04,488
Guardian of the Well, are you in here?

768
00:58:05,827 --> 00:58:08,957
<i>Yes, you let me in here,</i>

769
00:58:09,039 --> 00:58:11,039
<i>so I am very delighted.</i>

770
00:58:12,000 --> 00:58:15,590
I'm sorry, but this place isn't for you.

771
00:58:15,921 --> 00:58:17,421
Please return to your place.

772
00:58:18,966 --> 00:58:20,546
<i>I do not wish to return.</i>

773
00:58:22,010 --> 00:58:23,850
What made you so furious?

774
00:58:23,929 --> 00:58:27,349
If you tell me,
I will try my best to resolve it.

775
00:58:27,599 --> 00:58:31,399
<i>I do not wish to go back.
I do not wish to go.</i>

776
00:58:31,728 --> 00:58:33,268
What did you say?

777
00:58:34,147 --> 00:58:36,187
<i>I ran away from there.</i>

778
00:58:37,275 --> 00:58:38,775
<i>I am scared.</i>

779
00:58:54,084 --> 00:58:57,674
<i>I am scared of getting abandoned.</i>

780
00:58:59,715 --> 00:59:01,795
<i>I've never dried up</i>

781
00:59:02,384 --> 00:59:04,724
<i>and have given the people fresh water.</i>

782
00:59:07,055 --> 00:59:09,635
<i>No matter how much they took,
I was filled up again.</i>

783
00:59:10,142 --> 00:59:13,312
<i>I gave them water to make alcohol
and let them make money.</i>

784
00:59:13,979 --> 00:59:17,519
Please let our <i>makgeolli</i> business
become a success.

785
00:59:18,275 --> 00:59:21,185
<i>However, I can no longer fill up</i>

786
00:59:21,278 --> 00:59:24,278
<i>as much water as they want.</i>

787
00:59:28,201 --> 00:59:30,451
<i>I am continuously getting dried up.</i>

788
00:59:31,329 --> 00:59:35,249
<i>I ran away before I dry up completely
and get abandoned</i>

789
00:59:35,333 --> 00:59:36,753
<i>like an empty pond.</i>

790
00:59:38,170 --> 00:59:41,170
<i>I chose to abandon them first</i>

791
00:59:41,715 --> 00:59:43,715
<i>while they could still miss me.</i>

792
01:00:31,139 --> 01:00:34,849
<i>What is it like to be
at the ugly bottom of my soul?</i>

793
01:00:36,520 --> 01:00:37,810
I am saddened.

794
01:00:38,563 --> 01:00:41,483
<i>I am sorry that I'm in a place
where I am not welcomed.</i>

795
01:00:41,942 --> 01:00:44,192
<i>But I have nowhere else to go.</i>

796
01:00:57,332 --> 01:00:58,922
<i>Please help me.</i>

797
01:01:20,939 --> 01:01:25,189
<i>I'm a lowly diety, but I'll return
the favor for your help.</i>

798
01:01:28,822 --> 01:01:30,702
<i>Since you saw my fears already,</i>

799
01:01:31,158 --> 01:01:33,868
<i>I'll show you yours.</i>

800
01:01:34,369 --> 01:01:36,539
<i>This will help you resolve your concerns.</i>

801
01:02:17,037 --> 01:02:18,287
Is that the moon?

802
01:02:21,541 --> 01:02:22,631
Chan-sung.

803
01:02:23,293 --> 01:02:24,423
Are you okay?

804
01:02:27,797 --> 01:02:28,917
I'm okay.

805
01:02:36,139 --> 01:02:37,679
I found a way.

806
01:03:22,352 --> 01:03:24,062
We found another one, sir!

807
01:03:39,995 --> 01:03:40,995
Move out of the way.

808
01:03:46,835 --> 01:03:49,205
<i>Today, five bodies that were buried
in secret</i>

809
01:03:49,296 --> 01:03:51,046
<i>were found on a hill.</i>

810
01:03:51,131 --> 01:03:53,761
<i>The police believe there might be
more bodies buried,</i>

811
01:03:53,842 --> 01:03:55,262
<i>and are continuing their search.</i>

812
01:03:55,343 --> 01:03:57,433
<i>According to the police, it'll take</i>

813
01:03:57,512 --> 01:03:58,812
-<i>a few more days</i>
-Here.

814
01:03:58,888 --> 01:04:00,598
<i>to identify the bodies,</i>

815
01:04:00,682 --> 01:04:02,812
<i>and it'll take over a week</i>

816
01:04:02,892 --> 01:04:05,272
<i>to find the causes of deaths.</i>

817
01:04:05,353 --> 01:04:08,983
There were serial murders.
They found five bodies.

818
01:04:09,399 --> 01:04:11,399
Really? Gosh.

819
01:04:11,901 --> 01:04:13,031
Bye.

820
01:04:17,949 --> 01:04:20,659
Wait a minute. How did they find out?

821
01:04:31,921 --> 01:04:34,841
We brought some guests.

822
01:04:47,228 --> 01:04:49,228
-Drink up, guys.
-Here.

823
01:04:49,314 --> 01:04:51,074
-Dig in.
-It's been a while.

824
01:04:51,149 --> 01:04:51,979
It's delicious.

825
01:04:52,067 --> 01:04:53,817
-This is expensive.
-You didn't change at all.

826
01:04:53,902 --> 01:04:55,152
-Do you think so?
-Here.

827
01:04:55,236 --> 01:04:56,446
You don't know Mi-ra, right?

828
01:04:56,529 --> 01:04:57,609
I know I look young.

829
01:04:57,739 --> 01:04:59,279
-Right?
-It's nice.

830
01:04:59,366 --> 01:05:01,366
-Mi-ra, you can drink soda.
-Why?

831
01:05:01,451 --> 01:05:03,501
-It's directly from the factory.
-Watch it.

832
01:05:04,454 --> 01:05:06,214
Hey, guys.

833
01:05:06,289 --> 01:05:07,369
Hello, Ji-won.

834
01:05:07,832 --> 01:05:08,832
Hey, Ji-won!

835
01:05:08,917 --> 01:05:10,337
-It's been a while.
-Hey.

836
01:05:10,418 --> 01:05:12,458
-It's been so long.
-Hello.

837
01:05:13,296 --> 01:05:15,716
-It's been so long.
-Hey, Ji-won!

838
01:05:15,799 --> 01:05:17,509
-What is going on?
-You're still the same.

839
01:05:17,592 --> 01:05:19,262
How did he come here?

840
01:05:19,386 --> 01:05:22,596
What? I called him
since he wasn't on the invitee list.

841
01:05:24,641 --> 01:05:25,851
Ji-won, sit here.

842
01:05:31,356 --> 01:05:33,016
It's nice to see you.

843
01:05:35,860 --> 01:05:37,280
Long time no see, Sanchez.

844
01:05:37,779 --> 01:05:38,859
Yes.

845
01:05:39,614 --> 01:05:41,164
I didn't know you'd show up here.

846
01:05:44,285 --> 01:05:46,245
There's someone I wanted to see.

847
01:05:47,038 --> 01:05:49,328
I heard Chan-sung is back in Korea too.

848
01:05:50,333 --> 01:05:51,753
Yes, he's back.

849
01:05:52,252 --> 01:05:54,502
I didn't know
you and Chan-sung were close.

850
01:05:55,213 --> 01:05:57,173
Of course we are. I know him well.

851
01:05:58,383 --> 01:06:01,853
He's a smart guy who's good at everything.

852
01:06:04,889 --> 01:06:07,519
Is he still the same? I want to see him.

853
01:06:28,913 --> 01:06:30,833
A chairman I was close to was

854
01:06:31,207 --> 01:06:33,747
nice enough to provide
a small spring in his villa.

855
01:06:34,252 --> 01:06:35,842
You'll be at peace here.

856
01:07:27,263 --> 01:07:29,933
The <i>makgeolli</i> from that village
will taste different now.

857
01:07:31,351 --> 01:07:33,141
They'll find a different source of water.

858
01:07:33,520 --> 01:07:36,270
Even if the water's taste changes,
not many will notice it

859
01:07:36,689 --> 01:07:38,319
as long as the label doesn't change.

860
01:07:39,901 --> 01:07:42,491
Their <i>makgeolli</i> used to be so good.

861
01:07:42,862 --> 01:07:46,952
It's upsetting and sad to think
I won't ever get to taste it again.

862
01:07:47,367 --> 01:07:49,037
He was sad too.

863
01:07:50,995 --> 01:07:55,115
He dried up the well as a punishment
because he was cross.

864
01:07:55,250 --> 01:07:56,250
Now he's sad?

865
01:07:57,919 --> 01:07:59,589
He told me he wasn't cross.

866
01:07:59,879 --> 01:08:01,629
If he wanted to punish them,

867
01:08:01,714 --> 01:08:03,554
he would've called on you
since you're stronger.

868
01:08:03,633 --> 01:08:05,473
Why would he call on a weak human like me?

869
01:08:11,975 --> 01:08:15,645
What did you see
at the bottom of the well?

870
01:08:19,566 --> 01:08:21,026
Fear.

871
01:08:21,776 --> 01:08:22,936
"Fear"?

872
01:08:23,236 --> 01:08:25,106
For seeing his weakness,

873
01:08:25,697 --> 01:08:27,567
he showed me

874
01:08:28,116 --> 01:08:29,486
what I fear,

875
01:08:30,410 --> 01:08:32,200
what I want to avoid

876
01:08:32,912 --> 01:08:34,252
and run away from right now.

877
01:08:39,377 --> 01:08:40,587
It was...

878
01:08:42,380 --> 01:08:43,670
very scary.

879
01:10:18,059 --> 01:10:20,139
Like how I could look into your dreams,

880
01:10:20,311 --> 01:10:21,521
you were able

881
01:10:22,355 --> 01:10:24,225
to see my fears, weren't you?

882
01:10:27,235 --> 01:10:30,025
Just like how I helped the Guardian
of the Well move to a safe place,

883
01:10:30,488 --> 01:10:31,608
you were

884
01:10:32,240 --> 01:10:34,160
only trying to put me in a safe place.

885
01:10:42,375 --> 01:10:43,745
You know what this is, don't you?

886
01:10:45,169 --> 01:10:46,249
It looks like a medicine.

887
01:10:46,337 --> 01:10:48,797
I thought it was strange
why Mago would suddenly give this to me.

888
01:10:49,882 --> 01:10:51,472
You asked her to give it to me, right?

889
01:10:52,009 --> 01:10:53,969
Think what you want.

890
01:10:56,180 --> 01:10:57,310
Chan-sung.

891
01:10:58,433 --> 01:11:00,143
I'll pray for your safety.

892
01:11:06,315 --> 01:11:07,435
No.

893
01:11:11,195 --> 01:11:14,275
I will get in danger
to make you feel uncomfortable.

894
01:11:15,867 --> 01:11:16,777
What?

895
01:11:21,372 --> 01:11:24,542
Chan-sung!
Do you know how precious that is?

896
01:11:25,668 --> 01:11:28,128
Do you know
how much I had to beg to get that?

897
01:11:28,212 --> 01:11:29,382
Jang Man-wol!

898
01:11:30,590 --> 01:11:32,550
No place is safe for me anymore.

899
01:11:35,178 --> 01:11:37,558
I will keep getting on your nerves
and get in danger.

900
01:11:37,638 --> 01:11:38,678
You must...

901
01:11:41,684 --> 01:11:43,314
keep protecting me.

902
01:12:42,995 --> 01:12:46,955
<i>But in fact, I was hoping you'd return.</i>

903
01:12:47,625 --> 01:12:49,875
<i>I won't let you vanish.</i>

904
01:12:49,961 --> 01:12:51,131
Trust me.

905
01:12:52,672 --> 01:12:56,092
<i>You brought both that woman
and Yeon-u to me.</i>

906
01:12:56,843 --> 01:12:58,803
Thank you, Chan-sung.

907
01:12:59,303 --> 01:13:01,853
<i>If Chan-sung didn't take the medicine,</i>

908
01:13:01,931 --> 01:13:04,231
<i>then he can probably see
the connections that were cut off.</i>

909
01:13:04,308 --> 01:13:07,648
<i>It's the past I have been hiding.
Please get rid of it.</i>

910
01:13:07,812 --> 01:13:11,112
<i>I brought a connection
from your past again.</i>

911
01:13:12,233 --> 01:13:14,243
Subtitle translation by Wayne Ryu

912
01:13:19,671 --> 01:13:20,961
You know what this is, don't you?

913
01:13:21,339 --> 01:13:22,469
It looks like a medicine.

914
01:13:22,548 --> 01:13:25,008
I thought it was strange
why Mago would suddenly give this to me.

915
01:13:26,094 --> 01:13:27,724
You asked her to give it to me, right?

916
01:13:28,179 --> 01:13:30,139
Think what you want.

917
01:13:32,308 --> 01:13:33,688
Chan-sung.

918
01:13:34,644 --> 01:13:36,274
I'll pray for your safety.

919
01:13:40,024 --> 01:13:41,114
No.

920
01:13:44,153 --> 01:13:47,203
I will get in danger
to make you feel uncomfortable.

921
01:13:48,825 --> 01:13:49,865
What?

922
01:13:54,038 --> 01:13:57,208
Chan-sung!
Do you know how precious that is?

923
01:13:58,376 --> 01:14:00,916
Do you know
how much I had to beg to get that?

924
01:14:01,004 --> 01:14:02,054
Jang Man-wol!

925
01:14:03,298 --> 01:14:05,088
No place is safe for me anymore.

926
01:14:07,885 --> 01:14:10,215
I will keep getting on your nerves
and get in danger.

927
01:14:10,305 --> 01:14:11,305
You must...

928
01:14:14,392 --> 01:14:15,772
keep protecting me.

929
01:14:27,572 --> 01:14:29,202
Does this medicine belong to you?

930
01:14:37,790 --> 01:14:39,250
It's yours, isn't it?

931
01:14:40,293 --> 01:14:44,173
Why would you pick it up
and give it back to me now?

932
01:14:44,714 --> 01:14:47,844
I thought you dropped it,
so I brought it back as a thank-you.

933
01:14:49,761 --> 01:14:50,971
Thank you.

934
01:14:51,679 --> 01:14:54,219
You brought back something
that's very precious.

935
01:14:54,891 --> 01:14:57,311
You may go ahead and rest.

936
01:15:00,396 --> 01:15:03,856
Isn't this something
that will help you get rid of your fears?

937
01:15:04,067 --> 01:15:06,147
Well, yes.

938
01:15:06,444 --> 01:15:08,954
Then, I hope you take it and feel at ease.

939
01:15:16,663 --> 01:15:17,663
See?

940
01:15:18,373 --> 01:15:20,503
Even the deity says
you should take the medicine.

941
01:15:20,625 --> 01:15:23,245
He's very slow-witted.

942
01:15:24,045 --> 01:15:26,755
He's giving you advice as someone
who ran away and found peace.

943
01:15:27,131 --> 01:15:28,131
Eat it.

944
01:15:31,010 --> 01:15:32,510
You must've forgotten something.

945
01:15:32,595 --> 01:15:35,515
If you get attacked by a ghost that holds
a deep grudge, you could even die.

946
01:15:36,099 --> 01:15:38,979
You almost died recently because of me.

947
01:15:40,019 --> 01:15:42,359
Don't get yourself in trouble.
Just live peacefully.

948
01:15:43,398 --> 01:15:44,398
Eat it.

949
01:15:45,108 --> 01:15:46,108
If I eat that,

950
01:15:48,778 --> 01:15:50,318
I won't be able to see you anymore.

951
01:15:55,410 --> 01:15:57,120
You also must've forgotten something.

952
01:15:57,787 --> 01:15:59,707
I can see through you.

953
01:16:14,095 --> 01:16:15,555
If I don't take care of you,

954
01:16:16,431 --> 01:16:18,561
you'll only end up becoming more spiteful.

955
01:16:18,641 --> 01:16:20,391
I'd rather get myself in trouble

956
01:16:21,310 --> 01:16:23,060
and stop you from ending up that way.

957
01:16:24,063 --> 01:16:25,193
I...

958
01:16:26,566 --> 01:16:28,146
I can't let that...

959
01:16:29,902 --> 01:16:31,112
happen to you.

960
01:16:40,371 --> 01:16:41,541
So,

961
01:16:42,206 --> 01:16:45,916
I'm going to stay beside you
and keep an eye on you.

962
01:16:49,046 --> 01:16:50,466
Mr. Koo Chan-sung?

963
01:16:52,258 --> 01:16:53,548
What is it this time?

964
01:16:55,678 --> 01:16:59,058
What brings you to my father's villa?

965
01:17:07,315 --> 01:17:10,815
You asked my father for a favor
back when he was alive?

966
01:17:11,527 --> 01:17:14,987
Yes, he let me borrow the pond
in his botanical garden.

967
01:17:15,531 --> 01:17:19,371
Did you set free a pet fish or something?

968
01:17:19,494 --> 01:17:22,294
It's something very special.
It'll give out a lot of good energy.

969
01:17:22,622 --> 01:17:26,832
My father told me about you
a couple of times before he passed away.

970
01:17:26,918 --> 01:17:28,668
That you helped him out a lot.

971
01:17:29,420 --> 01:17:32,510
We're here to take care of his belongings.

972
01:17:32,590 --> 01:17:33,760
I see.

973
01:17:35,551 --> 01:17:36,841
BAEKGU

974
01:17:39,597 --> 01:17:41,097
This is mine.

975
01:17:41,432 --> 01:17:44,772
I spent a lot of time with him here
when I was a kid.

976
01:17:45,978 --> 01:17:47,098
-Mom.
-Yes?

977
01:17:47,188 --> 01:17:50,018
Look what I found in this book.

978
01:17:52,610 --> 01:17:55,320
My goodness, when was this?

979
01:17:55,696 --> 01:17:57,906
Father looks so young in this photo.

980
01:18:00,660 --> 01:18:02,330
I miss him so much.

981
01:18:02,703 --> 01:18:03,753
If you want,

982
01:18:03,830 --> 01:18:06,960
you can write a letter and give it to me.

983
01:18:07,291 --> 01:18:08,791
The hotel I work at provides

984
01:18:08,876 --> 01:18:11,796
a special service where you can send
letters to the ones you miss.

985
01:18:26,435 --> 01:18:29,435
I thought you would've already left,
but I guess you waited for me.

986
01:18:30,106 --> 01:18:31,566
Because I don't like driving.

987
01:18:34,986 --> 01:18:37,906
If you don't like driving,
why did you buy so many cars?

988
01:18:37,989 --> 01:18:39,279
Because they're pretty.

989
01:18:40,199 --> 01:18:43,079
I'm going to buy
every single car you sold.

990
01:18:43,160 --> 01:18:44,160
With what money?

991
01:18:44,245 --> 01:18:46,115
You said you're willing
to go through trouble,

992
01:18:46,205 --> 01:18:47,865
so let me be a little cheap
while I'm at it.

993
01:18:47,957 --> 01:18:49,497
Give me the painting of Baekdu Mountain.

994
01:18:52,461 --> 01:18:55,511
Do you think I'll give that to you?
That was my severance pay.

995
01:18:55,590 --> 01:18:58,550
I just dropped it at your place.
It's mine, so give it back.

996
01:19:00,553 --> 01:19:03,143
There's a famous restaurant nearby
that once aired on TV.

997
01:19:03,431 --> 01:19:04,521
Let's go there.

998
01:19:05,474 --> 01:19:06,854
A famous restaurant?

999
01:19:08,436 --> 01:19:10,936
It must be baffling to hear me
talk about food in this situation.

1000
01:19:11,022 --> 01:19:13,022
You must be feeling furious.

1001
01:19:13,816 --> 01:19:15,436
That's exactly how I felt.

1002
01:19:17,570 --> 01:19:18,570
Let's go.

1003
01:19:25,161 --> 01:19:28,791
If we don't get to the restaurant
before it closes because of you,

1004
01:19:30,541 --> 01:19:33,091
that painting of Baekdu Mountain

1005
01:19:33,502 --> 01:19:35,462
will never be yours.

1006
01:19:49,018 --> 01:19:53,478
Your favorite celebrity,
Kim Jun-hyun, came here as well.

1007
01:19:56,400 --> 01:19:58,950
Oh, right. You should take a photo.

1008
01:20:00,613 --> 01:20:02,493
THE GUYS WHO DIED AFTER EATING

1009
01:20:06,619 --> 01:20:09,039
I'LL VISIT EVERY FAMOUS RESTAURANT
IN THIS COUNTRY

1010
01:20:11,582 --> 01:20:15,422
There aren't any naengmyeon restaurants

1011
01:20:15,503 --> 01:20:17,173
or any shopping malls around here.

1012
01:20:17,254 --> 01:20:18,924
Why don't you just
come back to Myeong-dong?

1013
01:20:19,006 --> 01:20:20,626
This place is too far away from my house.

1014
01:20:20,716 --> 01:20:22,966
Just work at the hotel
you used to work at.

1015
01:20:23,594 --> 01:20:25,014
The owner of that hotel

1016
01:20:25,471 --> 01:20:27,721
seemed very fond of you earlier.

1017
01:20:28,057 --> 01:20:31,847
I'm just interested in being liked
by my current boss.

1018
01:20:32,728 --> 01:20:33,978
And to make that happen,

1019
01:20:36,065 --> 01:20:37,315
I'm going to challenge myself.

1020
01:20:40,444 --> 01:20:43,534
Promise that you'll reinstate me
if I eat this in one bite.

1021
01:20:44,615 --> 01:20:45,945
Are you serious?

1022
01:20:46,826 --> 01:20:50,996
Kim Jun-hyun can eat
the entire thing in one bite.

1023
01:20:51,080 --> 01:20:52,460
You're no match for him.

1024
01:20:53,833 --> 01:20:55,633
You'll never be able to do it.

1025
01:21:00,881 --> 01:21:02,551
Just give me my job back if I succeed.

1026
01:21:08,556 --> 01:21:09,636
Don't even bother.

1027
01:21:11,475 --> 01:21:13,265
I don't watch his shows anymore.

1028
01:21:16,313 --> 01:21:19,073
You used to like him so much.
You abandoned him as well?

1029
01:21:19,150 --> 01:21:20,150
Yes.

1030
01:21:20,943 --> 01:21:22,613
So if you succeed,

1031
01:21:23,112 --> 01:21:25,872
you should become a comedian
instead of coming back to my hotel.

1032
01:21:29,535 --> 01:21:30,995
Is it that easy to give up?

1033
01:21:31,078 --> 01:21:32,658
No, not really.

1034
01:21:33,247 --> 01:21:37,167
He's on almost every TV channel.

1035
01:21:40,463 --> 01:21:43,343
I hope the food here
tastes really horrible

1036
01:21:44,383 --> 01:21:45,973
so that I'll never think of it again.

1037
01:22:16,248 --> 01:22:17,878
THE GUYS WHO DIED AFTER EATING

1038
01:22:48,781 --> 01:22:51,031
I told you to park the car and go.
Why are you following me?

1039
01:22:51,117 --> 01:22:52,697
To make it hard for you

1040
01:22:52,785 --> 01:22:54,575
to give up on me.

1041
01:22:57,665 --> 01:22:59,575
But right now,
I'm here to meet the chairman.

1042
01:22:59,667 --> 01:23:01,667
His granddaughter asked me
to give this to him.

1043
01:23:01,752 --> 01:23:02,922
I'll give it to him.

1044
01:23:03,003 --> 01:23:05,213
No, how can I trust you?

1045
01:23:05,297 --> 01:23:07,377
I'll give it to him myself.

1046
01:23:07,466 --> 01:23:10,426
I'm the owner of this hotel,
and you recently got fired.

1047
01:23:11,011 --> 01:23:12,011
Ms. Jang.

1048
01:23:14,598 --> 01:23:16,478
Mr. Koo, I see you also came to work.

1049
01:23:16,559 --> 01:23:19,309
He's not the manager here.
He's just visiting.

1050
01:23:19,395 --> 01:23:21,055
Go ahead and meet the chairman.

1051
01:23:22,606 --> 01:23:24,226
I have something urgent to tell you.

1052
01:23:40,749 --> 01:23:45,169
Are you saying the guests
you guys brought were all murdered?

1053
01:23:45,254 --> 01:23:48,844
Yes, we saw them buried in the woods.
And there were no graves.

1054
01:23:56,849 --> 01:23:59,179
I called the police from a payphone.

1055
01:23:59,268 --> 01:24:00,978
It was on the news.

1056
01:24:01,061 --> 01:24:04,691
A number of corpses have been found.
Everyone says it's serial killing.

1057
01:24:04,773 --> 01:24:07,153
Judging from what the guests are saying,

1058
01:24:07,234 --> 01:24:09,824
it seems to be true that they were
all killed by the same person.

1059
01:24:09,904 --> 01:24:11,824
They all said it was a stranger to them,

1060
01:24:11,906 --> 01:24:14,066
but they all agreed
that it was a young man.

1061
01:24:14,158 --> 01:24:15,368
It's that guy.

1062
01:24:15,451 --> 01:24:18,791
I'm sure
the owner of that car is the killer.

1063
01:24:23,459 --> 01:24:25,039
I jotted down the license plate number.

1064
01:24:25,127 --> 01:24:26,917
-Let's find him and--
-Don't get involved.

1065
01:24:28,756 --> 01:24:30,416
Hyeon-jung already called the police,

1066
01:24:30,507 --> 01:24:32,717
and the fact that the bodies were found
was on the news.

1067
01:24:32,801 --> 01:24:35,931
Since the killer is alive,
the police can catch him.

1068
01:24:36,013 --> 01:24:39,933
All we have to do is take good care of
the dead victims until they can see that

1069
01:24:40,017 --> 01:24:41,687
and leave at peace.

1070
01:24:42,686 --> 01:24:45,686
Make sure to install a television
if they want to watch the news.

1071
01:24:46,148 --> 01:24:47,898
Give them access to our Wi-Fi network

1072
01:24:47,983 --> 01:24:49,283
so that they can search the web.

1073
01:24:49,401 --> 01:24:50,241
Yes, ma'am.

1074
01:25:02,206 --> 01:25:03,116
Are you okay?

1075
01:25:03,749 --> 01:25:05,079
The police will catch him.

1076
01:25:05,376 --> 01:25:07,626
Hyeon-jung, you called the police,

1077
01:25:07,711 --> 01:25:11,591
so the cops must be so confused now.

1078
01:25:14,301 --> 01:25:16,511
The call was made from this payphone,

1079
01:25:16,637 --> 01:25:20,847
but no one was caught
on the security camera over there.

1080
01:25:22,142 --> 01:25:23,192
Was it a ghost?

1081
01:25:23,978 --> 01:25:25,558
It's so odd.

1082
01:25:28,065 --> 01:25:30,105
Ghosts don't exist.

1083
01:25:30,943 --> 01:25:34,073
What's odder to me is
how payphones like this still exist.

1084
01:25:37,950 --> 01:25:39,450
Do you have any change?

1085
01:25:39,868 --> 01:25:41,368
Oh, yes. Just a second.

1086
01:25:43,998 --> 01:25:45,038
Here you go.

1087
01:25:47,167 --> 01:25:48,747
Thank you.

1088
01:25:50,754 --> 01:25:51,924
I'll give you this in return.

1089
01:26:00,180 --> 01:26:01,140
It's all right.

1090
01:26:01,390 --> 01:26:03,600
Gosh, no. If you lose this,

1091
01:26:04,101 --> 01:26:06,311
you'll stay a bachelor.

1092
01:26:06,729 --> 01:26:09,689
For the rest of your life.

1093
01:26:09,773 --> 01:26:12,073
Forever.

1094
01:26:12,192 --> 01:26:15,112
You won't even be able to date anyone.

1095
01:26:15,571 --> 01:26:18,781
Don't ever lose it.

1096
01:26:22,828 --> 01:26:24,038
Hey.

1097
01:26:25,247 --> 01:26:26,617
Right, yes.

1098
01:26:26,707 --> 01:26:28,077
Wait, ma'am.

1099
01:26:32,755 --> 01:26:33,875
What was that about?

1100
01:26:37,134 --> 01:26:41,014
For the rest of your life.

1101
01:26:41,263 --> 01:26:44,733
Forever.

1102
01:26:54,568 --> 01:26:56,528
DEAR GRANDFATHER WHOM I MISS DEARLY

1103
01:26:56,612 --> 01:26:58,202
I'M SO HAPPY I CAN WRITE YOU A LETTER

1104
01:27:00,115 --> 01:27:01,325
Your granddaughter is

1105
01:27:01,408 --> 01:27:03,908
very sad about not being by your side
in your final moments.

1106
01:27:03,994 --> 01:27:06,164
She was studying abroad at the time.

1107
01:27:06,830 --> 01:27:08,290
I get to see her like this.

1108
01:27:08,832 --> 01:27:10,132
I owe it all to you.

1109
01:27:11,627 --> 01:27:14,047
I guess you rode your motorcycle earlier.
That suits you.

1110
01:27:15,422 --> 01:27:16,592
You think so?

1111
01:27:16,673 --> 01:27:18,883
I never got to do this when I was alive,

1112
01:27:18,967 --> 01:27:20,587
thinking it'd be frowned upon.

1113
01:27:20,969 --> 01:27:22,759
Thanks to you,
I get to enjoy this as well.

1114
01:27:22,846 --> 01:27:25,136
I'm glad to see you happy.

1115
01:27:28,685 --> 01:27:31,145
Isn't my granddaughter so pretty?

1116
01:27:34,733 --> 01:27:35,653
Yes, she is.

1117
01:27:40,447 --> 01:27:43,447
-Do you have a girlfriend?
-Pardon?

1118
01:27:43,534 --> 01:27:46,664
My granddaughter doesn't have
a boyfriend yet.

1119
01:27:46,870 --> 01:27:49,710
Her name is Jeong Ji-eun. She's 25.

1120
01:27:49,790 --> 01:27:53,130
She's just been studying,
so she can't pick out good guys.

1121
01:27:53,669 --> 01:27:57,969
I always wanted to find
a nice, reliable guy for her.

1122
01:28:01,301 --> 01:28:02,801
Oh, I see.

1123
01:28:04,388 --> 01:28:06,968
I'm sure she'll meet
a wonderful man. Don't worry.

1124
01:28:07,349 --> 01:28:09,309
I'll be off, then.

1125
01:28:20,279 --> 01:28:22,659
Chan-sung doesn't have a girlfriend.

1126
01:28:22,739 --> 01:28:25,699
You seemed curious
about that nice, reliable guy.

1127
01:28:26,785 --> 01:28:27,785
Is that so?

1128
01:28:28,162 --> 01:28:31,872
Then shall I tell you more
about Chan-sung?

1129
01:28:39,381 --> 01:28:42,381
Shall I tell Chan-sung
to take care of this since he's here?

1130
01:28:42,551 --> 01:28:43,551
Forget it.

1131
01:28:43,927 --> 01:28:46,967
Ms. Jang, there you are.

1132
01:28:47,055 --> 01:28:48,095
What is it?

1133
01:28:48,182 --> 01:28:50,182
I curried favor with Chairman Wang

1134
01:28:50,267 --> 01:28:51,597
as per your order.

1135
01:28:51,685 --> 01:28:54,145
Good. So have you found out anything?

1136
01:28:54,563 --> 01:28:56,863
He entrusted me
with taking care of something

1137
01:28:56,940 --> 01:28:58,570
that is still bothering him very much.

1138
01:28:59,485 --> 01:29:02,485
Look at you. Well done, Seon-bi.

1139
01:29:03,405 --> 01:29:05,445
You sure are a capable man.

1140
01:29:05,532 --> 01:29:07,872
Once again, you proved
to be such a useful asset.

1141
01:29:07,951 --> 01:29:09,081
Chairman Wang

1142
01:29:09,286 --> 01:29:11,286
has a granddaughter
that he absolutely adores.

1143
01:29:11,580 --> 01:29:14,880
He's still upset
that he couldn't find a nice guy for her,

1144
01:29:14,958 --> 01:29:17,088
so I promised him
I'll hook her up with a nice guy.

1145
01:29:17,169 --> 01:29:18,379
You'll find a guy for her!

1146
01:29:18,462 --> 01:29:21,052
Great. If all goes well,
he'll buy you a nice suit.

1147
01:29:21,131 --> 01:29:24,381
He's a chairman. He won't stop there.

1148
01:29:25,093 --> 01:29:26,223
You're absolutely right.

1149
01:29:26,303 --> 01:29:28,353
You'll find a nice guy
for his granddaughter.

1150
01:29:28,430 --> 01:29:31,310
He'll have to take care of this
for us at the very least.

1151
01:29:31,391 --> 01:29:33,061
You have nothing to worry about now.

1152
01:29:33,143 --> 01:29:34,273
I knew it.

1153
01:29:34,353 --> 01:29:38,363
You're the ace of our hotel,
without a doubt.

1154
01:29:38,899 --> 01:29:42,489
And Chairman Wang really likes
the guy I recommended.

1155
01:29:42,569 --> 01:29:44,739
My gosh, Mr. Kim.

1156
01:29:44,821 --> 01:29:47,371
I'm sure all the work at the bar
keeps you busy enough.

1157
01:29:47,449 --> 01:29:50,119
When did you have time to go out,
meet people, and recommend someone?

1158
01:29:50,410 --> 01:29:54,120
I don't have time to meet new people.
I only know one guy.

1159
01:29:55,332 --> 01:29:56,212
What?

1160
01:29:57,626 --> 01:29:59,336
I recommended Koo Chan-sung.

1161
01:30:02,631 --> 01:30:04,881
You mean the manager of our hotel,

1162
01:30:05,133 --> 01:30:07,013
Koo Chan-sung?

1163
01:30:07,135 --> 01:30:09,215
He's no longer our manager.

1164
01:30:09,513 --> 01:30:11,223
I know it's been bothering you as well.

1165
01:30:11,306 --> 01:30:13,056
Let's marry him off to the granddaughter.

1166
01:30:13,141 --> 01:30:16,101
He won't ignore us if he marries
into that rich family thanks to us.

1167
01:30:16,186 --> 01:30:18,806
We'll get money from Chairman Wang
and Chan-sung.

1168
01:30:18,897 --> 01:30:20,317
We'll kill two birds with one stone.

1169
01:30:21,608 --> 01:30:23,148
Did he leave already?

1170
01:30:23,235 --> 01:30:26,025
I have to give him
the granddaughter's number.

1171
01:30:27,030 --> 01:30:28,370
Just trust me.

1172
01:30:30,284 --> 01:30:31,494
Where did he go?

1173
01:30:33,620 --> 01:30:37,120
That dunderhead.

1174
01:30:41,628 --> 01:30:42,668
Did Mr. Koo leave?

1175
01:30:42,754 --> 01:30:44,554
No, I didn't see him leaving.

1176
01:30:44,840 --> 01:30:48,180
That means he's still here.
All right, catch you later.

1177
01:30:52,055 --> 01:30:53,845
TO MS. JANG MAN-WOL, I LOVE YOU

1178
01:30:55,559 --> 01:30:57,189
She still has this.

1179
01:31:13,035 --> 01:31:15,495
-You're still here.
-I will leave soon.

1180
01:31:16,788 --> 01:31:19,168
Mr. Koo?

1181
01:31:19,875 --> 01:31:21,165
What is going on?

1182
01:31:21,251 --> 01:31:23,381
Is he in Ms. Jang's office?

1183
01:31:26,089 --> 01:31:26,969
Mr. Koo!

1184
01:31:28,675 --> 01:31:29,925
He's not here.

1185
01:31:30,010 --> 01:31:31,680
What's the matter?

1186
01:31:31,762 --> 01:31:32,802
I have to...

1187
01:31:32,888 --> 01:31:34,008
My gosh.

1188
01:31:34,431 --> 01:31:36,641
Would he be in the garden?

1189
01:31:38,101 --> 01:31:40,231
What's with him? Goodness.

1190
01:31:47,110 --> 01:31:48,820
Do we have to stay like this?

1191
01:31:51,907 --> 01:31:53,527
Why do we have to do this?

1192
01:31:54,159 --> 01:31:55,699
You don't like money, right?

1193
01:31:55,786 --> 01:31:57,536
You prefer plain things

1194
01:31:57,829 --> 01:31:59,039
over fancy things.

1195
01:31:59,122 --> 01:32:00,372
You love that tacky poop...

1196
01:32:01,208 --> 01:32:04,038
I mean, you like dull colors like brown.

1197
01:32:04,628 --> 01:32:05,588
Right?

1198
01:32:05,671 --> 01:32:09,221
Is this your way of pressuring me to
give you the painting of Baekdu Mountain?

1199
01:32:12,052 --> 01:32:13,512
Now I see.

1200
01:32:14,513 --> 01:32:16,523
You are greedy for money.

1201
01:32:16,598 --> 01:32:20,348
Yes, I am. I want to make a lot of money.

1202
01:32:20,435 --> 01:32:22,395
Is being money-grubbing
something to brag about?

1203
01:32:22,479 --> 01:32:24,309
Is that what they taught you at Harvard?

1204
01:32:25,524 --> 01:32:28,284
Yes, MBA programs teach you
how you can earn money.

1205
01:32:28,360 --> 01:32:29,530
Okay, you show-off.

1206
01:32:29,611 --> 01:32:31,281
You greedy fraud from Harvard.

1207
01:32:31,363 --> 01:32:33,453
-What--
-I hope you become filthy rich.

1208
01:32:33,532 --> 01:32:34,992
Then own a hotel!

1209
01:32:35,367 --> 01:32:36,277
Get out!

1210
01:32:37,953 --> 01:32:39,003
Why...

1211
01:32:48,338 --> 01:32:51,128
She's so mad at me
for not giving her the painting.

1212
01:32:58,598 --> 01:32:59,638
Jang Man-wol.

1213
01:33:01,268 --> 01:33:03,188
I'll give you back
the painting of Baekdu Mountain.

1214
01:33:06,148 --> 01:33:09,478
And as for the medicine,
you should keep it.

1215
01:33:12,863 --> 01:33:14,493
It'll be the last way

1216
01:33:16,158 --> 01:33:17,988
for me to run away

1217
01:33:19,786 --> 01:33:21,826
and for you to abandon me.

1218
01:33:33,258 --> 01:33:35,968
I'll wait for your call
to reinstate me back at the hotel.

1219
01:33:39,014 --> 01:33:40,564
And the meal we had today.

1220
01:33:41,850 --> 01:33:43,140
I enjoyed it.

1221
01:33:45,020 --> 01:33:46,100
Let's...

1222
01:33:47,272 --> 01:33:48,692
go and have another meal there.

1223
01:34:32,692 --> 01:34:35,402
My wife hasn't been home
for several days now.

1224
01:34:35,487 --> 01:34:37,107
That's why I'm calling you.

1225
01:34:37,823 --> 01:34:41,123
If she calls you,
please tell her that I'm sorry.

1226
01:34:41,451 --> 01:34:43,871
Please tell her to come back home.

1227
01:34:44,746 --> 01:34:45,746
Thank you.

1228
01:34:59,261 --> 01:35:00,261
Gosh.

1229
01:35:01,763 --> 01:35:02,603
No!

1230
01:35:03,265 --> 01:35:04,385
Honey!

1231
01:35:04,808 --> 01:35:06,018
Oh, no!

1232
01:35:06,184 --> 01:35:08,984
What happened to you? What is this? Honey.

1233
01:35:09,271 --> 01:35:11,361
What happened to you? Honey.

1234
01:35:11,856 --> 01:35:12,856
What...

1235
01:35:13,275 --> 01:35:14,935
What is this? Why...

1236
01:35:15,026 --> 01:35:16,946
Wait. Why...

1237
01:35:22,158 --> 01:35:24,828
It's just like the tip.
There's a body here.

1238
01:35:25,829 --> 01:35:28,539
You're under arrest for murdering
your wife, Lee Do-yeon.

1239
01:35:28,623 --> 01:35:31,383
-I didn't kill her.
-You have the right to remain silent.

1240
01:35:31,459 --> 01:35:33,209
And you have the right to an attorney.

1241
01:35:34,337 --> 01:35:37,547
What about the shovel?
Get the shovel. The one with dirt on it.

1242
01:35:42,721 --> 01:35:45,181
There you go. That's it.

1243
01:35:46,308 --> 01:35:48,808
You ought to arrest a serial killer.

1244
01:35:53,857 --> 01:35:55,147
Bye.

1245
01:36:08,747 --> 01:36:10,117
Darn it.

1246
01:36:11,541 --> 01:36:13,841
Why do you hate Seol Ji-won so much?

1247
01:36:15,128 --> 01:36:17,918
Did something happen
between you and him in the States?

1248
01:36:18,882 --> 01:36:20,882
Not between just the two of us.
Among three people.

1249
01:36:21,718 --> 01:36:23,178
Chan-sung was involved too?

1250
01:36:23,261 --> 01:36:25,181
It was after you went back to Korea.

1251
01:36:25,263 --> 01:36:28,683
A Korean international student
committed suicide in Boston.

1252
01:36:29,100 --> 01:36:31,900
But there was a ridiculous rumor
she killed herself because of me.

1253
01:36:31,978 --> 01:36:33,728
What? Because of you?

1254
01:36:33,813 --> 01:36:36,363
No way. Who would believe that?

1255
01:36:36,483 --> 01:36:37,483
People did.

1256
01:36:37,692 --> 01:36:39,532
That ridiculous rumor snowballed.

1257
01:36:39,611 --> 01:36:43,321
Later, people said that
I was a rich piece of trash

1258
01:36:43,657 --> 01:36:46,327
who toyed with the poor
International student and made her

1259
01:36:46,409 --> 01:36:48,409
do something nasty with foreign friends.

1260
01:36:50,997 --> 01:36:55,127
Afterward, on an online forum,
people started to bet

1261
01:36:56,086 --> 01:36:58,126
on whether I'd kill myself or not.

1262
01:37:00,840 --> 01:37:02,430
And the guy who set up the whole thing...

1263
01:37:02,634 --> 01:37:03,804
Seol Ji-won?

1264
01:37:10,517 --> 01:37:11,727
It's you, isn't it?

1265
01:37:12,560 --> 01:37:15,480
You're the one who spread
the rumor about Jae-in.

1266
01:37:15,605 --> 01:37:17,605
I just said

1267
01:37:17,691 --> 01:37:21,241
that I saw you invite her to the party
you had with rich European friends.

1268
01:37:21,569 --> 01:37:22,779
She...

1269
01:37:24,406 --> 01:37:25,866
She came to work as a waitress.

1270
01:37:25,949 --> 01:37:28,029
She said she needed money for her tuition,

1271
01:37:28,243 --> 01:37:30,873
-so I got her a job--
-She could have done something else.

1272
01:37:35,583 --> 01:37:38,843
Don't get so worked up
because no one will believe you.

1273
01:37:39,212 --> 01:37:42,222
Actually, everyone was fed up
with your righteous acts as a rich guy.

1274
01:37:48,888 --> 01:37:49,888
Keep your chin up.

1275
01:37:50,181 --> 01:37:53,351
I made a bet that you'd live.

1276
01:38:40,231 --> 01:38:42,861
What are you doing here?
I've been looking all over for you.

1277
01:38:46,654 --> 01:38:47,954
Let's go eat.

1278
01:38:55,371 --> 01:38:57,671
When I was in misery
and almost thought about dying,

1279
01:38:57,749 --> 01:38:59,419
Chan-sung came to me.

1280
01:39:01,211 --> 01:39:04,801
That day, he took the box with the gun
and went to see Seol Ji-won.

1281
01:39:04,881 --> 01:39:08,341
After that, Seol Ji-won went back
to Korea all of a sudden.

1282
01:39:08,635 --> 01:39:10,545
What did Chan-sung do that day?

1283
01:39:12,680 --> 01:39:14,020
I don't know that either.

1284
01:39:15,058 --> 01:39:19,558
Well, anyway, after that,
he always found me to have a meal with me

1285
01:39:19,646 --> 01:39:21,356
until the rumor died down.

1286
01:39:21,648 --> 01:39:23,938
That's how you two got so close.

1287
01:39:30,824 --> 01:39:32,164
Who threw these out?

1288
01:39:32,700 --> 01:39:34,450
Today's not the day. It's tomorrow.

1289
01:39:35,328 --> 01:39:36,158
I'm sorry.

1290
01:39:37,413 --> 01:39:39,873
Chan-sung, I brought
some pizza for you. Go wash up.

1291
01:39:39,958 --> 01:39:40,958
Thank you.

1292
01:39:41,209 --> 01:39:42,839
The recycling trash goes out on Saturdays.

1293
01:39:50,468 --> 01:39:53,718
Don't tell Chan-sung that we met
Seol Ji-won at the gathering today.

1294
01:39:53,805 --> 01:39:56,175
I don't want Chan-sung to have
anything to do with that jerk.

1295
01:39:56,266 --> 01:39:58,096
Okay. I won't tell him.

1296
01:40:02,605 --> 01:40:06,145
It's my loss. There's no guy
better than Chan-sung.

1297
01:40:08,194 --> 01:40:11,574
I think Chan-sung would make
the best grandson-in-law.

1298
01:40:17,078 --> 01:40:20,868
I understand that you like Chan-sung,
but you have already passed away.

1299
01:40:20,957 --> 01:40:24,287
How can you pass on your message
to your granddaughter?

1300
01:40:24,377 --> 01:40:27,377
That brings me to my next point.
I'd like to make

1301
01:40:27,463 --> 01:40:30,053
a special request to your hotel.

1302
01:40:30,884 --> 01:40:33,684
The bartender told me all about it.

1303
01:40:33,761 --> 01:40:36,351
I heard that your hotel provides
a dream call service

1304
01:40:36,431 --> 01:40:39,231
where the dead can talk
to the living in their dreams.

1305
01:40:44,230 --> 01:40:47,030
I heard that I could pay you
with the money from this world.

1306
01:40:47,108 --> 01:40:50,188
I just remembered an asset
I forgot to take care of.

1307
01:41:30,860 --> 01:41:32,030
Grandpa.

1308
01:41:42,997 --> 01:41:44,957
You received my photo?

1309
01:41:46,251 --> 01:41:51,301
The guy who gave me this photo is
really my cup of tea.

1310
01:41:52,924 --> 01:41:54,514
Mr. Koo Chan-sung?

1311
01:41:54,968 --> 01:41:56,338
That's right.

1312
01:41:56,844 --> 01:42:01,774
I really hope that young man
can be your husband.

1313
01:42:02,308 --> 01:42:04,638
Let me tell you about the guy.

1314
01:42:09,274 --> 01:42:10,864
Your time is up.

1315
01:42:10,942 --> 01:42:14,032
It was very expensive to make this call.
Is it supposed to be this short?

1316
01:42:14,112 --> 01:42:16,162
Then, why don't you make another call?

1317
01:42:19,033 --> 01:42:20,993
The rule says
you can only make a call a day.

1318
01:42:21,286 --> 01:42:23,996
You must think about other guests too.

1319
01:42:32,755 --> 01:42:35,295
But I think you told her
all the important parts.

1320
01:42:38,636 --> 01:42:42,056
Ms. Jang, will Mr. Koo really

1321
01:42:42,140 --> 01:42:44,310
marry into the wealthy family?

1322
01:42:45,727 --> 01:42:47,977
Kids these days
rarely listen to old people.

1323
01:42:48,313 --> 01:42:51,323
She never listened to her grandfather.
Why would she now?

1324
01:42:58,740 --> 01:43:01,580
My grandfather came to me
in my dream last night.

1325
01:43:01,659 --> 01:43:03,869
He told me that he received my photo.

1326
01:43:03,953 --> 01:43:06,753
Really? You must've been happy.

1327
01:43:09,834 --> 01:43:11,044
Also,

1328
01:43:12,211 --> 01:43:14,461
he told me something else.

1329
01:43:15,006 --> 01:43:20,046
I really hope that young man
can be your husband.

1330
01:43:30,688 --> 01:43:31,558
Use this.

1331
01:43:35,735 --> 01:43:38,355
Could you please clean this for us?

1332
01:43:39,113 --> 01:43:40,113
Thank you.

1333
01:43:44,369 --> 01:43:45,579
Mr. Koo?

1334
01:43:46,287 --> 01:43:47,617
Have you eaten?

1335
01:43:49,665 --> 01:43:52,665
I'd like to talk more
about my grandfather with you.

1336
01:43:54,962 --> 01:43:57,012
Sure, let's grab a bite to eat.

1337
01:43:58,383 --> 01:43:59,513
What do you like?

1338
01:44:03,513 --> 01:44:04,933
Here he comes!

1339
01:44:05,306 --> 01:44:06,596
Did you really murder your wife?

1340
01:44:06,682 --> 01:44:08,392
Why did you kill the others
that were buried?

1341
01:44:08,476 --> 01:44:10,226
Are there any more victims?

1342
01:44:10,311 --> 01:44:13,361
What was the reason behind these murders?

1343
01:44:13,439 --> 01:44:15,779
-Is there an accomplice?
-Are there any more victims?

1344
01:44:15,858 --> 01:44:18,188
-Please say a few words.
-Any words?

1345
01:44:18,528 --> 01:44:20,238
-Over here!
-Sir!

1346
01:44:20,321 --> 01:44:21,701
MAN ARRESTED FOR MURDERING HIS WIFE

1347
01:44:21,781 --> 01:44:23,071
That's not right.

1348
01:44:23,324 --> 01:44:26,374
The guy had a smaller build.

1349
01:44:26,869 --> 01:44:27,789
What guy?

1350
01:44:35,670 --> 01:44:38,380
I don't think this man is the killer.

1351
01:44:38,589 --> 01:44:41,549
All we have to do is find the car 0963.

1352
01:44:41,717 --> 01:44:43,137
What? 0963?

1353
01:44:43,386 --> 01:44:45,006
Did you memorize the license plate number?

1354
01:44:45,263 --> 01:44:46,103
Yes.

1355
01:44:46,764 --> 01:44:48,314
Forget it like you forget English words.

1356
01:44:48,391 --> 01:44:49,851
Darn.

1357
01:44:53,479 --> 01:44:56,069
My friend owns the place,
and the food is quite tasty.

1358
01:44:56,149 --> 01:44:58,069
-It's Mr. Koo.
-Sanchez!

1359
01:44:59,068 --> 01:45:00,318
-How have you been?
-And you?

1360
01:45:00,403 --> 01:45:03,073
-Do you know Sanchez?
-We're in the same yacht club.

1361
01:45:03,531 --> 01:45:05,281
-It's been a while.
-Really?

1362
01:45:05,366 --> 01:45:06,946
What a coincidence.

1363
01:45:07,410 --> 01:45:09,910
-I should visit there sometime.
-You won't be allowed in.

1364
01:45:10,788 --> 01:45:11,788
That's not true.

1365
01:45:11,873 --> 01:45:13,963
You could if you had a hotel of your own.

1366
01:45:14,041 --> 01:45:15,631
I was going to talk

1367
01:45:15,710 --> 01:45:19,420
about the car with Mr. Koo,
but he seems busy.

1368
01:45:19,505 --> 01:45:22,505
Actually, he doesn't
work at the hotel anymore.

1369
01:45:22,592 --> 01:45:23,592
What?

1370
01:45:24,510 --> 01:45:26,640
-He'll marry into a rich family.
-I can use my experience

1371
01:45:26,721 --> 01:45:27,811
as a hotel manager

1372
01:45:27,889 --> 01:45:30,309
to greet the members
and help with their baggage.

1373
01:45:30,641 --> 01:45:33,481
-That's nice.
-And see them off later.

1374
01:45:37,148 --> 01:45:39,688
KOO CHAN-SUNG

1375
01:45:41,319 --> 01:45:43,739
I'll wait for your call
to reinstate me back at the hotel.

1376
01:45:47,658 --> 01:45:50,288
Ms. Jang!

1377
01:45:50,411 --> 01:45:54,121
They met!

1378
01:45:55,458 --> 01:45:57,248
The blind date happened.

1379
01:45:58,419 --> 01:46:00,589
What? They met?

1380
01:46:00,671 --> 01:46:03,171
I saw Mr. Koo meeting
Chairman Wang's granddaughter.

1381
01:46:03,424 --> 01:46:06,684
I haven't seen him smile so widely before.

1382
01:46:10,306 --> 01:46:11,306
Of course.

1383
01:46:22,193 --> 01:46:24,243
Who knew he had such an ambition?

1384
01:46:25,947 --> 01:46:27,027
I'm not sure about that.

1385
01:46:27,114 --> 01:46:29,494
He's always been the friendly type.

1386
01:46:29,575 --> 01:46:31,365
You should see for yourself then.

1387
01:46:31,452 --> 01:46:33,162
They agreed to meet tomorrow as well.

1388
01:46:33,579 --> 01:46:35,869
Mr. Koo invited her over to his house.

1389
01:46:35,957 --> 01:46:38,537
That means
she's going to meet Mr. Koo's parents.

1390
01:46:40,086 --> 01:46:41,956
Mr. Koo's father passed away, remember?

1391
01:46:43,130 --> 01:46:44,760
I'm not sure about his mother.

1392
01:46:44,882 --> 01:46:46,632
Is his mother still alive?

1393
01:46:47,969 --> 01:46:49,259
How should I know?

1394
01:46:49,595 --> 01:46:51,885
You're always bitter when this comes up.

1395
01:46:52,557 --> 01:46:55,267
Anyway, wouldn't it be great
if this leads to Koo Chan-sung

1396
01:46:55,351 --> 01:46:56,811
getting his own family?

1397
01:46:56,894 --> 01:46:59,484
You know how warm he's been to our guests.

1398
01:46:59,647 --> 01:47:03,527
This must be the work of good karma.
And I'm so happy for him.

1399
01:47:07,029 --> 01:47:08,029
Is that so?

1400
01:47:08,864 --> 01:47:10,244
May he be full of luck then.

1401
01:47:28,426 --> 01:47:30,716
Are you cleaning
because Ji-eun is coming tomorrow?

1402
01:47:31,345 --> 01:47:33,595
Yes, it should be clean.

1403
01:47:39,228 --> 01:47:42,148
Dating someone else
will help him forget about Man-wol.

1404
01:47:42,815 --> 01:47:44,935
Still, he plays it big.

1405
01:47:45,026 --> 01:47:48,356
He only goes for a woman
who has a hotel of her own.

1406
01:48:26,192 --> 01:48:28,742
There's a book here
that's haunted by a ghost.

1407
01:48:29,320 --> 01:48:30,660
That's ridiculous.

1408
01:48:30,821 --> 01:48:33,121
My cousin's a librarian here,
and she told me.

1409
01:48:33,741 --> 01:48:37,241
The ghost that donated it
comes along whenever you pull it out.

1410
01:48:37,662 --> 01:48:38,832
Sounds like fun.

1411
01:48:39,872 --> 01:48:41,672
Where's the book?
Let's post it on social media.

1412
01:48:52,635 --> 01:48:53,835
-This way?
-Yes.

1413
01:48:55,137 --> 01:48:56,307
Okay, I'm filming.

1414
01:48:57,848 --> 01:48:59,138
-Pull it out.
-Got it.

1415
01:49:03,854 --> 01:49:06,364
It won't come out. I'm not kidding!

1416
01:49:06,440 --> 01:49:08,530
-Come on already.
-It really must be haunted.

1417
01:49:20,121 --> 01:49:21,211
What's wrong?

1418
01:49:22,039 --> 01:49:24,539
Seol? Are you all right?

1419
01:49:25,209 --> 01:49:26,209
Seol?

1420
01:49:27,545 --> 01:49:28,995
Hey! Are you all right?

1421
01:49:29,088 --> 01:49:30,298
EXISTENCE AND TIME

1422
01:49:33,342 --> 01:49:36,802
Are you all right? Seol, wake up!

1423
01:49:37,179 --> 01:49:39,059
Come on. Please.

1424
01:49:39,807 --> 01:49:41,057
Wake up.

1425
01:49:44,270 --> 01:49:46,860
If Chan-sung hasn't taken the medicine,

1426
01:49:46,939 --> 01:49:49,359
then he can probably see
the connections that were cut off.

1427
01:49:49,525 --> 01:49:51,895
It's the side effect of
being able to see ghosts.

1428
01:49:53,028 --> 01:49:55,908
I hear you made two incompatible souls
cross their paths.

1429
01:49:56,782 --> 01:50:00,872
It's always fun to make enemies
of previous lives meet again.

1430
01:50:01,370 --> 01:50:04,330
They're drawn to each other
because of leftover feelings.

1431
01:50:06,584 --> 01:50:08,004
My goodness.

1432
01:50:09,170 --> 01:50:10,880
How pretty!

1433
01:50:18,137 --> 01:50:19,677
-Are you getting in?
-Yes.

1434
01:50:27,438 --> 01:50:28,518
Excuse me.

1435
01:50:30,441 --> 01:50:31,691
Is this yours?

1436
01:50:35,321 --> 01:50:36,361
Thank you.

1437
01:51:11,148 --> 01:51:12,188
Look.

1438
01:51:13,067 --> 01:51:14,437
Just look at this.

1439
01:51:14,527 --> 01:51:16,357
This is all because of your pen.

1440
01:51:16,487 --> 01:51:18,157
This is brand new, you know.

1441
01:51:18,239 --> 01:51:19,989
I'm terribly sorry. What can I do?

1442
01:51:20,074 --> 01:51:21,374
You can pay for the dry-cleaning.

1443
01:51:21,992 --> 01:51:24,832
I'm busy today,
so give me your number instead.

1444
01:51:25,120 --> 01:51:26,120
Sorry?

1445
01:51:29,583 --> 01:51:30,753
Hold on.

1446
01:51:33,212 --> 01:51:34,422
This ink is black.

1447
01:51:36,173 --> 01:51:39,263
You're right. It's very black

1448
01:51:40,553 --> 01:51:41,973
even though it's pink on the outside.

1449
01:51:44,473 --> 01:51:45,433
Forget it then.

1450
01:51:47,601 --> 01:51:48,441
Excuse me.

1451
01:51:54,733 --> 01:51:56,283
This pen is important to me,

1452
01:51:56,360 --> 01:51:58,450
so let me pay for the cleaning
for getting it back to me.

1453
01:52:02,700 --> 01:52:04,080
May I have your number?

1454
01:52:07,079 --> 01:52:08,209
Sure thing.

1455
01:52:25,639 --> 01:52:28,429
So this is the library
the chairman established.

1456
01:52:29,018 --> 01:52:32,308
Yes, this must be
why my grandfather came to me

1457
01:52:32,396 --> 01:52:34,186
in my dream.

1458
01:52:39,028 --> 01:52:42,818
I wanted this would happen
the moment I met you too.

1459
01:52:43,115 --> 01:52:45,325
I'm sure my grandfather
will be very happy.

1460
01:52:48,954 --> 01:52:49,834
Shall we go?

1461
01:53:00,132 --> 01:53:01,632
Are you happy now?

1462
01:53:02,092 --> 01:53:04,302
They make a nice couple.

1463
01:53:04,386 --> 01:53:06,676
Then, as you promised,

1464
01:53:06,764 --> 01:53:08,604
I will keep that money.

1465
01:53:09,725 --> 01:53:11,015
You can keep watching them here.

1466
01:53:49,515 --> 01:53:50,975
You are so pretty.

1467
01:53:51,058 --> 01:53:52,478
You are like a princess.

1468
01:53:52,559 --> 01:53:53,559
Really?

1469
01:53:53,936 --> 01:53:55,896
-I hardly recognized you.
-Thanks.

1470
01:53:56,647 --> 01:53:58,147
How is your mother?

1471
01:53:58,607 --> 01:54:00,357
She is healthy and doing well.

1472
01:54:00,442 --> 01:54:02,742
-Good. I need to visit her.
-Yes.

1473
01:54:02,820 --> 01:54:04,820
This is Koo Chan-sung.

1474
01:54:05,572 --> 01:54:06,912
Hello.

1475
01:54:06,991 --> 01:54:08,991
Nice to meet you. I am Koo Chan-sung.

1476
01:54:17,793 --> 01:54:18,923
Jang Man-wol.

1477
01:54:24,174 --> 01:54:25,474
Why are you here?

1478
01:54:25,551 --> 01:54:27,721
Chairman Wang wanted to see
his granddaughter.

1479
01:54:27,845 --> 01:54:30,805
He paid a high price for the dream call,
so this is a special service.

1480
01:54:30,889 --> 01:54:32,469
You can ignore this and go.

1481
01:54:32,683 --> 01:54:35,483
Since you are here,
why don't you look around the library?

1482
01:54:36,145 --> 01:54:37,685
There are many good books

1483
01:54:38,022 --> 01:54:39,402
and nice paintings here.

1484
01:54:39,481 --> 01:54:40,691
Forget it.

1485
01:54:41,191 --> 01:54:42,441
I'm going back.

1486
01:54:44,319 --> 01:54:45,989
Come on. Take a look around the library.

1487
01:54:46,530 --> 01:54:47,950
There's a nice painting here.

1488
01:54:56,707 --> 01:54:58,247
I sold this.

1489
01:54:58,959 --> 01:55:01,169
If we waited for the memorial hall
to be built,

1490
01:55:01,253 --> 01:55:03,013
you'd probably collapse first.

1491
01:55:04,590 --> 01:55:07,890
So his granddaughter and I decided
to hang it here.

1492
01:55:12,389 --> 01:55:15,809
I came here to sell this.
What did you come to sell?

1493
01:55:16,393 --> 01:55:18,983
What kind of a deal did you make
with the chairman without me?

1494
01:55:19,104 --> 01:55:20,864
And the "high price for the dream call"?

1495
01:55:24,651 --> 01:55:25,941
You don't need to know.

1496
01:55:26,904 --> 01:55:28,704
There are many good paintings here?

1497
01:55:28,864 --> 01:55:30,664
Why don't we look at them?

1498
01:55:32,576 --> 01:55:34,616
How much did you rip off
from the chairman?

1499
01:55:34,703 --> 01:55:37,083
Just a little. Very little.

1500
01:55:37,873 --> 01:55:39,883
Actually,
that's the chairman's painting as well.

1501
01:55:39,958 --> 01:55:42,248
I feel a bit like committing fraud.

1502
01:55:42,544 --> 01:55:45,214
You are a greedy fraud
from Harvard anyway.

1503
01:55:45,589 --> 01:55:46,879
A fraud?

1504
01:55:47,299 --> 01:55:49,219
You keep calling me that. Take it back.

1505
01:55:49,301 --> 01:55:51,801
-I don't want to.
-You don't want to?

1506
01:55:51,887 --> 01:55:55,307
That's not what matters.
Take back what you said.

1507
01:55:57,476 --> 01:56:00,346
That guy called Chan-sung

1508
01:56:00,854 --> 01:56:02,234
seemed nice.

1509
01:56:02,773 --> 01:56:04,783
Are you seeing him?

1510
01:56:07,069 --> 01:56:08,819
I wanted to.

1511
01:56:10,280 --> 01:56:12,160
He told me there is someone else.

1512
01:56:26,421 --> 01:56:28,551
The cafeteria of this library
is not bad at all.

1513
01:56:29,591 --> 01:56:30,591
Isn't it?

1514
01:56:31,093 --> 01:56:33,223
I came here often with my father
when I was young.

1515
01:56:33,387 --> 01:56:34,597
The food was also good then.

1516
01:56:35,097 --> 01:56:36,467
Did you live around here back then?

1517
01:56:36,598 --> 01:56:40,348
Father wanted to send me
to an elementary school around here.

1518
01:56:40,435 --> 01:56:43,225
The rent in this neighborhood was so high
that we couldn't get a room.

1519
01:56:43,564 --> 01:56:44,944
But we came here often.

1520
01:56:45,149 --> 01:56:46,649
Because the food was cheap and tasty.

1521
01:56:47,067 --> 01:56:49,697
Did you only live with your father
from the start?

1522
01:56:50,070 --> 01:56:52,990
Yes. The reason my name is Chan-sung is

1523
01:56:53,073 --> 01:56:56,833
that the only person who wanted
me to be born was my father.

1524
01:56:56,910 --> 01:57:00,330
He felt bad about that
so he named me Chan-sung.

1525
01:57:01,290 --> 01:57:04,380
But he didn't know
Chinese characters very well.

1526
01:57:04,793 --> 01:57:06,383
So my name means a brilliant star.

1527
01:57:11,175 --> 01:57:13,175
The reason your father sold you

1528
01:57:13,927 --> 01:57:15,757
was not to save himself.

1529
01:57:16,305 --> 01:57:17,755
It was because of you.

1530
01:57:19,057 --> 01:57:20,847
Because you would be alone without him.

1531
01:57:23,812 --> 01:57:27,272
Of course I know that.
He was my only family.

1532
01:57:34,698 --> 01:57:37,238
If you are finished,
let's go and read some books.

1533
01:57:37,743 --> 01:57:38,623
Books?

1534
01:57:40,203 --> 01:57:42,213
I can't do that in this condition.

1535
01:57:42,497 --> 01:57:46,627
-Why?
-My clothes don't suit books.

1536
01:57:46,710 --> 01:57:48,500
What's that got to do with books?

1537
01:57:48,587 --> 01:57:50,257
It has everything to do with them.

1538
01:57:50,339 --> 01:57:52,839
Look.
I have to take a photo at the library

1539
01:57:52,925 --> 01:57:54,375
to post it on my social media.

1540
01:57:54,468 --> 01:57:57,508
What I'm wearing isn't appropriate.

1541
01:57:57,596 --> 01:57:58,676
God...

1542
01:57:59,014 --> 01:58:01,224
Have some coffee and wait for me.

1543
01:58:01,308 --> 01:58:03,058
I'll get changed and come right back.

1544
01:58:03,393 --> 01:58:05,353
There's no need for that. Sit down.

1545
01:58:05,896 --> 01:58:08,106
I didn't mean to go to read books.

1546
01:58:08,273 --> 01:58:10,363
I want us to find the ghost
attached to a book.

1547
01:58:15,238 --> 01:58:17,778
There is a rumor
that there is a ghost around here.

1548
01:58:17,866 --> 01:58:19,696
The director of the library
is very worried.

1549
01:58:19,910 --> 01:58:22,410
If there really is a ghost,
we should take it to the hotel.

1550
01:58:22,704 --> 01:58:24,924
There is a book with a ghost?

1551
01:58:25,165 --> 01:58:26,165
Yes.

1552
01:58:26,249 --> 01:58:28,709
The rumor is that the ghost
donated the book before.

1553
01:58:28,835 --> 01:58:31,875
She was an elementary school principal
and she died not long ago.

1554
01:58:32,047 --> 01:58:33,337
Her family donated her books.

1555
01:58:33,423 --> 01:58:35,183
The book must have been precious to her.

1556
01:58:35,717 --> 01:58:36,837
I don't know.

1557
01:58:37,135 --> 01:58:40,595
Most people easily throw away
things they used to care about.

1558
01:58:40,681 --> 01:58:43,061
They protect things they want
to hide with their life.

1559
01:58:43,600 --> 01:58:46,730
That ghost must have got nervous
when so many people came

1560
01:58:46,812 --> 01:58:48,862
to pull the book out because of the rumor.

1561
01:58:48,939 --> 01:58:50,769
What's there to hide in the book?

1562
01:58:51,149 --> 01:58:52,939
It's probably her emergency money.

1563
01:58:56,613 --> 01:58:57,743
Gosh.

1564
01:58:58,824 --> 01:59:00,834
She speeds up only when it's about money.

1565
01:59:02,536 --> 01:59:05,456
You're the human, so you pull it out.
The ghost won't come out if I do.

1566
01:59:08,500 --> 01:59:10,000
Existence and Time.

1567
01:59:10,544 --> 01:59:14,094
Nobody would want to read a book
with that title and look.

1568
01:59:14,172 --> 01:59:15,382
I read it.

1569
01:59:15,465 --> 01:59:16,925
I'm sure you did.

1570
01:59:17,009 --> 01:59:19,549
Since you're such a smarty-pants,
Koo Chan-sung.

1571
01:59:19,636 --> 01:59:21,636
You're so great.

1572
01:59:22,264 --> 01:59:25,234
Right. I read it to show off.

1573
01:59:26,059 --> 01:59:27,389
But it was difficult to understand.

1574
01:59:27,477 --> 01:59:30,477
I've been alive for over 1,000 years,
trying to kill time.

1575
01:59:30,939 --> 01:59:34,609
Even I don't know
what is existence or time.

1576
01:59:35,152 --> 01:59:37,862
You've only lived for about 30 years,
so how could you know?

1577
01:59:39,072 --> 01:59:42,872
Let's see what this book tells
about the time.

1578
01:59:43,618 --> 01:59:45,868
The ghost might not appear if I'm here.

1579
01:59:46,079 --> 01:59:47,619
I'll be near the bookshelf in the back.

1580
02:00:05,807 --> 02:00:07,267
You can see me?

1581
02:00:10,062 --> 02:00:11,902
Yes, I can see you.

1582
02:00:12,522 --> 02:00:13,942
What are you doing here?

1583
02:00:15,025 --> 02:00:17,145
I don't want anyone to read this book.

1584
02:00:17,360 --> 02:00:20,240
Is there something you cherish
in this book?

1585
02:00:22,115 --> 02:00:23,695
Or is it something you want to hide?

1586
02:00:26,453 --> 02:00:28,833
Can you get rid of something
inside the book?

1587
02:00:29,706 --> 02:00:30,666
I will help you.

1588
02:00:31,291 --> 02:00:33,631
To do that, I have to take out the book.

1589
02:01:18,046 --> 02:01:19,756
It's the past I have been hiding.

1590
02:01:24,719 --> 02:01:27,009
My family must not find out about it.

1591
02:01:28,223 --> 02:01:29,683
Please get rid of it.

1592
02:01:52,622 --> 02:01:54,002
The lady we just saw...

1593
02:01:57,294 --> 02:01:58,844
I think she's my mother.

1594
02:02:11,725 --> 02:02:13,635
I have never seen her.

1595
02:02:14,060 --> 02:02:15,810
I didn't even know she passed away.

1596
02:02:19,316 --> 02:02:21,856
I didn't know
my father sent these photos to her.

1597
02:02:24,446 --> 02:02:27,366
CHAN-SUNG AND I ARE GOING TO THE US

1598
02:02:30,952 --> 02:02:32,412
It wasn't something she cherished.

1599
02:02:33,747 --> 02:02:35,417
It was something she wanted to hide.

1600
02:02:41,713 --> 02:02:42,923
I guess...

1601
02:02:44,925 --> 02:02:46,585
she really didn't want me to be born.

1602
02:03:08,531 --> 02:03:10,581
You volunteered to go through trouble.

1603
02:03:10,825 --> 02:03:12,615
That's why you ended up
finding out about this.

1604
02:03:12,786 --> 02:03:14,906
It's just useless and upsetting.

1605
02:03:16,665 --> 02:03:18,245
What? Am I wrong?

1606
02:03:18,667 --> 02:03:21,127
Are you going to say you felt happy
to see your mother?

1607
02:03:21,211 --> 02:03:23,801
Do you want to take her to the hotel,
so you could be a filial son?

1608
02:03:25,465 --> 02:03:26,925
Do you think I'd want to do that?

1609
02:03:28,260 --> 02:03:29,260
Good.

1610
02:03:29,803 --> 02:03:31,763
Give me that. Let me put it back.

1611
02:03:32,222 --> 02:03:35,182
We'll just let that ghost
stay there forever.

1612
02:03:35,267 --> 02:03:36,307
That's not...

1613
02:03:37,352 --> 02:03:38,812
what I want either.

1614
02:03:39,771 --> 02:03:41,311
Then what do you want?

1615
02:03:41,815 --> 02:03:44,395
You ended up going through this
because I made you see ghosts,

1616
02:03:44,484 --> 02:03:47,034
-I should at least do something for you.
-I'm just sad...

1617
02:03:48,780 --> 02:03:51,870
that I wasn't able to feel happy
when I got to meet my mom...

1618
02:03:54,327 --> 02:03:55,497
for the first time.

1619
02:04:01,960 --> 02:04:03,710
Just let me grieve for now.

1620
02:04:23,273 --> 02:04:24,613
Never mind. Just go.

1621
02:05:01,394 --> 02:05:04,484
Did something happen?
Why do you look so upset?

1622
02:05:05,023 --> 02:05:06,073
Well...

1623
02:05:07,275 --> 02:05:09,525
I just feel a little sad.

1624
02:05:13,031 --> 02:05:15,951
I'm glad you're here. I'll cheer you up.

1625
02:05:16,201 --> 02:05:18,081
Let's go. I'll buy you a drink.

1626
02:05:22,957 --> 02:05:24,747
Hey, you lost a button.

1627
02:05:25,001 --> 02:05:26,671
Where did you lose it?

1628
02:05:27,629 --> 02:05:29,549
You're making me feel sorry for you.

1629
02:05:49,818 --> 02:05:51,568
Was she trying to console me?

1630
02:05:54,322 --> 02:05:55,452
Sanchez.

1631
02:05:55,657 --> 02:05:58,737
Hey, Mi-ra. I was just about
to leave with Chan-sung.

1632
02:05:58,827 --> 02:06:00,327
What? Chan-sung's here?

1633
02:06:02,205 --> 02:06:04,495
I don't think you can join us today.

1634
02:06:04,582 --> 02:06:06,252
You'll have to eat alone.

1635
02:06:06,334 --> 02:06:09,674
I have company.
Someone will be here to eat with me.

1636
02:06:09,754 --> 02:06:10,924
-Really?
-Yes.

1637
02:06:20,598 --> 02:06:22,728
Gosh, this place is nice.

1638
02:07:05,435 --> 02:07:06,935
What's going on?

1639
02:07:09,481 --> 02:07:11,901
Chan-sung, say hello. He's Park Yeong-su.

1640
02:07:26,748 --> 02:07:29,378
I helped him find something
that means a lot to him.

1641
02:07:29,459 --> 02:07:30,749
So he's treating me to a meal.

1642
02:07:34,380 --> 02:07:35,470
He died...

1643
02:07:36,466 --> 02:07:37,836
because of you.

1644
02:07:38,510 --> 02:07:39,510
What?

1645
02:07:41,513 --> 02:07:44,183
I know, right? His looks are to die for.

1646
02:07:44,265 --> 02:07:45,475
My gosh, Mi-ra.

1647
02:07:46,893 --> 02:07:48,903
He's a cop.

1648
02:07:50,647 --> 02:07:52,567
I heard you're going to leave
with Sanchez.

1649
02:07:52,815 --> 02:07:53,975
See you later.

1650
02:08:03,326 --> 02:08:05,616
What's wrong? Do you know him?

1651
02:08:07,247 --> 02:08:08,327
No, I don't know him.

1652
02:08:09,374 --> 02:08:10,544
But Jang Man-wol does.

1653
02:08:11,626 --> 02:08:12,626
Man-wol?

1654
02:08:13,127 --> 02:08:14,747
Does he know her too?

1655
02:08:16,047 --> 02:08:17,547
No, he probably doesn't.

1656
02:08:21,261 --> 02:08:24,641
Sanchez, I don't think
I can drink today. I'm sorry.

1657
02:08:25,598 --> 02:08:26,638
It's okay.

1658
02:08:35,817 --> 02:08:38,857
Tell me if Chan-sung ever told you
anything personal about his life.

1659
02:08:39,445 --> 02:08:41,855
Does he have any relatives
that he keeps in touch with?

1660
02:08:41,948 --> 02:08:44,578
What about his friends? Who else is
he friends with other than Sanchez?

1661
02:08:50,206 --> 02:08:52,326
No one knows anything? Seriously?

1662
02:08:52,458 --> 02:08:54,878
Mr. Koo always stuck by your side...

1663
02:08:55,795 --> 02:08:58,205
I mean, he always spent time with you.

1664
02:08:58,298 --> 02:08:59,418
Don't you know anything?

1665
02:09:01,009 --> 02:09:04,299
It's natural that I don't know since I'm
his boss, but his colleagues should.

1666
02:09:04,554 --> 02:09:07,854
How can you be so indifferent
to your colleague?

1667
02:09:11,603 --> 02:09:12,483
Seon-bi.

1668
02:09:12,937 --> 02:09:15,857
You even recommended him to the chairman,
and yet you know nothing?

1669
02:09:15,940 --> 02:09:19,530
I only recommended him
because he has a kind heart--

1670
02:09:19,611 --> 02:09:22,361
Hyeon-jung,
weren't you pretty close to him?

1671
02:09:22,614 --> 02:09:25,414
Well, from what I remember,

1672
02:09:26,242 --> 02:09:27,662
Mr. Koo

1673
02:09:29,537 --> 02:09:31,247
likes the color brown.

1674
02:09:31,331 --> 02:09:32,751
Even I know that.

1675
02:09:37,462 --> 02:09:39,212
The Grim Reaper's here.

1676
02:09:39,797 --> 02:09:41,507
Will you stop nagging at them?

1677
02:09:42,133 --> 02:09:43,933
You don't seem to know anything either.

1678
02:09:44,010 --> 02:09:46,640
What about you then? Do you know anything?

1679
02:09:46,721 --> 02:09:47,761
You saw him very often.

1680
02:09:51,976 --> 02:09:54,846
I get that you guys are ghosts,

1681
02:09:55,063 --> 02:09:57,323
but you're all so cold-hearted.

1682
02:09:59,692 --> 02:10:02,822
Ms. Jang,
why don't you just ask him yourself?

1683
02:10:02,904 --> 02:10:04,864
He's here.

1684
02:10:25,635 --> 02:10:27,675
I thought you'd be sad for a long time.

1685
02:10:28,388 --> 02:10:29,928
I guess you're okay already.

1686
02:10:31,849 --> 02:10:33,349
I'm not okay yet.

1687
02:10:37,563 --> 02:10:39,073
But I came because of you.

1688
02:10:41,275 --> 02:10:42,275
Because of me?

1689
02:10:44,487 --> 02:10:45,697
I think...

1690
02:10:47,240 --> 02:10:49,660
I stirred up your existence and time
this time.

1691
02:10:54,789 --> 02:10:57,379
I met someone from your painful memory.

1692
02:11:09,470 --> 02:11:13,060
BEOMCHEON CENTRAL POLICE STATION

1693
02:11:34,620 --> 02:11:36,750
He used to be a thief.

1694
02:11:39,751 --> 02:11:41,381
But now, he's a cop.

1695
02:11:51,512 --> 02:11:53,852
You're living a good life again.

1696
02:11:58,352 --> 02:11:59,692
I'm glad.

1697
02:12:02,732 --> 02:12:04,232
What a relief.

1698
02:12:18,039 --> 02:12:19,329
Do you want to go

1699
02:12:20,416 --> 02:12:21,916
and talk to him?

1700
02:12:24,462 --> 02:12:25,592
No.

1701
02:12:26,756 --> 02:12:28,126
I'm nobody to him.

1702
02:12:29,217 --> 02:12:31,587
He was like a family to you.

1703
02:12:32,845 --> 02:12:34,425
Will you be okay?

1704
02:12:35,640 --> 02:12:37,310
I won't be okay.

1705
02:12:39,519 --> 02:12:40,809
It's a bit sad.

1706
02:12:42,855 --> 02:12:44,265
I brought a connection

1707
02:12:47,151 --> 02:12:49,151
from your past again.

1708
02:12:57,328 --> 02:12:58,498
Thank you.

1709
02:12:59,872 --> 02:13:01,082
Chan-sung.

1710
02:13:06,462 --> 02:13:09,132
-Let me see.
-Gosh. No.

1711
02:14:23,331 --> 02:14:24,711
The serial murder case.

1712
02:14:24,790 --> 02:14:27,000
You got the analysis report
on the dirt from the shovel, right?

1713
02:14:27,210 --> 02:14:28,210
Pardon?

1714
02:14:28,294 --> 02:14:31,014
Yes, the dirt is the same as that of
the hill where the bodies were found.

1715
02:14:31,088 --> 02:14:32,128
Right?

1716
02:14:32,215 --> 02:14:35,045
But why does that suspect keep denying
that he killed them?

1717
02:14:35,134 --> 02:14:37,094
This is giving me a headache.

1718
02:14:37,345 --> 02:14:38,635
But the thing is

1719
02:14:39,305 --> 02:14:41,845
he doesn't have any motives
other than his wife's murder.

1720
02:14:43,100 --> 02:14:45,350
He's a typical psychopath.

1721
02:14:45,853 --> 02:14:46,943
A murder fanatic.

1722
02:15:10,461 --> 02:15:11,421
The end.

1723
02:15:49,000 --> 02:15:52,960
So there's a problem with the stuff
the truck was carrying that day.

1724
02:15:53,296 --> 02:15:55,456
Everything arrived without a problem.

1725
02:15:58,301 --> 02:16:00,431
Check the name
of the reservation one more time.

1726
02:16:00,511 --> 02:16:03,391
The reservation with the truck, 3465,
was made

1727
02:16:03,472 --> 02:16:05,022
under Koo Chan-sung.

1728
02:16:08,102 --> 02:16:11,272
-Who?
-Isn't this Mr. Koo Chan-sung?

1729
02:16:14,650 --> 02:16:15,860
Koo Chan-sung?

1730
02:16:18,529 --> 02:16:19,489
No way.

1731
02:16:28,080 --> 02:16:29,370
Koo Chan-sung.

1732
02:16:30,333 --> 02:16:31,673
Koo Chan-sung.

1733
02:16:32,335 --> 02:16:34,415
Why am I running into you here?

1734
02:16:57,651 --> 02:16:58,651
Chan-sung.

1735
02:16:59,987 --> 02:17:01,697
Are you staying home today again?

1736
02:17:03,699 --> 02:17:06,369
-Yes.
-You're not going to the hotel?

1737
02:17:07,036 --> 02:17:09,156
You kept going there
and said you'd be reinstated.

1738
02:17:09,246 --> 02:17:10,866
I have unfinished business here.

1739
02:17:11,540 --> 02:17:12,830
I don't think

1740
02:17:13,542 --> 02:17:16,462
I can take care of the hotel guests
if I go in this state.

1741
02:17:36,357 --> 02:17:37,857
EXISTENCE AND TIME

1742
02:17:45,366 --> 02:17:48,696
Will I find an answer
once I'm done with this difficult book?

1743
02:17:48,786 --> 02:17:50,406
A way to console a guy

1744
02:17:51,372 --> 02:17:54,632
whose existence
and time he spent with his mom

1745
02:17:55,251 --> 02:17:56,631
have completely been denied.

1746
02:18:04,260 --> 02:18:07,390
Are you worried that the secret
you've been hiding would be exposed?

1747
02:18:09,306 --> 02:18:10,516
Don't worry.

1748
02:18:11,642 --> 02:18:13,982
Your son doesn't want that.

1749
02:18:17,982 --> 02:18:19,482
He's sad.

1750
02:18:21,360 --> 02:18:23,030
And I want to console him.

1751
02:18:25,072 --> 02:18:26,412
I need you.

1752
02:18:29,034 --> 02:18:30,164
I will

1753
02:18:31,287 --> 02:18:33,287
escort you to my hotel.

1754
02:18:43,174 --> 02:18:44,224
Reinstated.

1755
02:18:44,675 --> 02:18:47,295
Come to the hotel. Take Line Four.

1756
02:18:47,970 --> 02:18:51,930
A guest you must send off is waiting.

1757
02:18:52,933 --> 02:18:54,853
A guest I must send off?

1758
02:19:34,517 --> 02:19:37,057
Mr. Koo, congratulations
on your reinstatement.

1759
02:19:37,269 --> 02:19:39,019
You came back to Myeong-dong.

1760
02:19:39,104 --> 02:19:41,614
I like this place
way more than the other place.

1761
02:19:52,243 --> 02:19:53,953
I look forward to working with you again.

1762
02:20:07,341 --> 02:20:09,591
I thought he would marry
into the rich family.

1763
02:20:09,677 --> 02:20:12,137
He came back to this hotel of ghosts.

1764
02:20:12,346 --> 02:20:14,096
How could a man have no ambition?

1765
02:20:14,181 --> 02:20:16,891
Ms. Jang needs Mr. Koo.

1766
02:20:17,268 --> 02:20:19,898
Ambitious men aren't popular among ladies.

1767
02:20:20,771 --> 02:20:22,271
You're so behind the times.

1768
02:20:22,690 --> 02:20:26,860
Besides, I told you to stop
talking like a dinosaur.

1769
02:20:32,116 --> 02:20:33,906
I did change the way I talk.

1770
02:20:34,868 --> 02:20:36,618
Right? Gosh.

1771
02:20:59,101 --> 02:21:00,691
I'm sorry for having kept you waiting.

1772
02:21:04,982 --> 02:21:06,572
Thank you for coming.

1773
02:21:11,655 --> 02:21:13,275
May I keep

1774
02:21:14,908 --> 02:21:16,828
the photos from the book?

1775
02:21:20,539 --> 02:21:21,829
Could you do that?

1776
02:21:23,375 --> 02:21:24,495
I'm very...

1777
02:21:27,504 --> 02:21:28,674
sorry.

1778
02:22:27,147 --> 02:22:28,317
Goodbye.

1779
02:22:31,694 --> 02:22:32,744
Mother.

1780
02:23:24,329 --> 02:23:25,749
Did you see her off?

1781
02:23:28,083 --> 02:23:29,083
Yes.

1782
02:23:30,627 --> 02:23:33,797
I'm sorry I took the liberty
of bringing her here.

1783
02:23:36,383 --> 02:23:39,553
Thank you for bringing her here.

1784
02:23:41,096 --> 02:23:42,176
Also

1785
02:23:43,474 --> 02:23:44,984
for telling me to return.

1786
02:23:48,395 --> 02:23:51,815
It's embarrassing for me to say this,
but let's get things straight.

1787
02:23:52,775 --> 02:23:54,775
You didn't return because I told you to.

1788
02:23:55,360 --> 02:23:56,610
You did it for me.

1789
02:24:01,700 --> 02:24:05,120
I could've forced you to eat the medicine
so you could never return,

1790
02:24:07,039 --> 02:24:08,749
but I didn't do that.

1791
02:24:15,672 --> 02:24:17,722
I thought you returned as you pleased

1792
02:24:19,009 --> 02:24:21,929
every time I gave you a chance
to run away.

1793
02:24:24,723 --> 02:24:26,353
But in fact,

1794
02:24:28,310 --> 02:24:30,810
I was hoping you'd return.

1795
02:24:35,651 --> 02:24:39,071
I'm glad to hear you admit
that I wasn't the only clingy one,

1796
02:24:39,613 --> 02:24:40,913
wanting to return.

1797
02:24:50,666 --> 02:24:51,826
Chan-sung.

1798
02:24:53,919 --> 02:24:55,499
I'm going to use you.

1799
02:24:59,049 --> 02:25:01,089
You brought both that woman and Yeon-u

1800
02:25:02,302 --> 02:25:03,762
to me.

1801
02:25:05,973 --> 02:25:07,393
Which means

1802
02:25:09,810 --> 02:25:11,190
you'll bring him too.

1803
02:25:15,732 --> 02:25:17,402
Yes, probably.

1804
02:25:17,484 --> 02:25:19,194
I'm certain that you will.

1805
02:25:21,321 --> 02:25:22,531
And

1806
02:25:23,824 --> 02:25:25,534
I will never let him

1807
02:25:26,702 --> 02:25:29,122
pass by unscathed.

1808
02:25:29,913 --> 02:25:31,543
That's why you'll use me?

1809
02:25:31,623 --> 02:25:34,463
That's right. I'll be vicious and cunning.

1810
02:25:35,085 --> 02:25:36,495
And you may end up

1811
02:25:37,170 --> 02:25:40,800
being used, abused, and wrecked
because of me.

1812
02:25:41,133 --> 02:25:42,183
Are you...

1813
02:25:44,011 --> 02:25:46,351
-threatening me again to make me run--
-No.

1814
02:25:49,141 --> 02:25:50,431
Don't run away.

1815
02:25:53,979 --> 02:25:55,729
You've already made up your mind

1816
02:25:57,441 --> 02:25:59,741
to get on my nerves and get in danger.

1817
02:26:02,237 --> 02:26:03,817
Knowing that such danger

1818
02:26:04,531 --> 02:26:06,661
could lead to death,

1819
02:26:09,244 --> 02:26:10,704
stay by my side.

1820
02:26:14,625 --> 02:26:15,665
Even if I...

1821
02:26:17,878 --> 02:26:19,588
go berserk, do crazy things,

1822
02:26:21,089 --> 02:26:22,879
and vanish one day...

1823
02:26:27,220 --> 02:26:29,060
please stay by my side.

1824
02:26:33,602 --> 02:26:34,602
No.

1825
02:26:43,612 --> 02:26:45,822
I won't let you vanish.

1826
02:26:57,668 --> 02:26:58,878
Trust me.

1827
02:30:07,899 --> 02:30:11,109
It must be pretty hard
to miss something you can't see.

1828
02:30:11,194 --> 02:30:14,784
You, I'm going easy on you
because you have a soft heart.

1829
02:30:17,075 --> 02:30:19,405
You probably saw the flowers.
Why aren't you saying anything?

1830
02:30:20,453 --> 02:30:23,503
We have to go before Ms. Jang does,

1831
02:30:23,582 --> 02:30:25,542
so let's prepare ourselves for that day.

1832
02:30:26,459 --> 02:30:29,879
They look so pretty now.
Why must they fall?

1833
02:30:30,297 --> 02:30:31,507
It's sad.

1834
02:30:31,756 --> 02:30:33,046
Flowers bloom

1835
02:30:33,633 --> 02:30:35,553
only to fall.

1836
02:30:39,472 --> 02:30:41,472
Subtitle translation by Wayne Ryu
